00:08:21.980 --> 00:08:25.260
Microeconomics studies the behavior

00:08:25.260 --> 00:08:29.380
of individual economic agents and their

00:08:29.380 --> 00:08:32.400
interaction in individual markets.

00:08:33.420 --> 00:08:35.340
Individual economic agents can

00:08:35.340 --> 00:08:37.740
be, for example, a separate

00:08:37.740 --> 00:08:42.960
firm or a separate household.

00:08:43.060 --> 00:08:44.380
And the focus of microeconomics

00:08:44.380 --> 00:08:47.300
is on the prices and production volumes

00:08:47.300 --> 00:08:48.940
of individual goods, the choice

00:08:48.940 --> 00:08:50.980
of individual consumers, the

00:08:50.980 --> 00:08:53.560
output of resources of individual

00:08:53.560 --> 00:08:57.850
firms, and so on.

00:08:57.950 --> 00:09:00.070
Macroeconomics, in turn, studies

00:09:00.450 --> 00:09:03.110
the economy as a whole as a

00:09:03.110 --> 00:09:04.790
single system.

00:09:05.790 --> 00:09:08.110
And in the center of its attention

00:09:08.110 --> 00:09:10.010
such generalizing indicators

00:09:10.010 --> 00:09:12.070
of social production, such

00:09:12.070 --> 00:09:13.790
as the domestic product,

00:09:13.950 --> 00:09:16.290
economic growth, unemployment,

00:09:16.290 --> 00:09:18.370
inflation, and so on.

