01:02:02.840 --> 01:02:03.720
We read.

01:02:04.080 --> 01:02:07.140
The offer is the amount of goods

01:02:07.140 --> 01:02:10.440
that all producers can and want

01:02:10.440 --> 01:02:13.960
to produce and sell during

01:02:13.960 --> 01:02:17.020
a given time and under certain

01:02:17.020 --> 01:02:19.720
conditions.

01:02:20.020 --> 01:02:20.900
Well, the same thing.

01:02:21.260 --> 01:02:23.040
Demand is how much they want to buy,

01:02:23.480 --> 01:02:24.960
and supply is how much they want

01:02:24.960 --> 01:02:26.920
to produce and sell.

01:02:28.020 --> 01:02:29.520
Now the proposal factors.

01:02:29.800 --> 01:02:30.560
Let us look at them.

01:02:30.560 --> 01:02:32.620
There are a lot of them here too.

01:02:33.480 --> 01:02:37.960
The first factor is the price of this product.

01:02:39.040 --> 01:02:42.400
The second is the profitability of

01:02:42.740 --> 01:02:45.560
goods that are competitive to this

01:02:45.560 --> 01:02:47.220
product in production.

01:02:48.240 --> 01:02:49.700
I fear that this is not very clear,

01:02:49.920 --> 01:02:52.320
but we will look at it on a specific example.

01:02:52.560 --> 01:02:54.220
The third factor is not better.

01:02:54.600 --> 01:02:57.440
The profitability of goods supplementing

01:02:57.440 --> 01:02:59.700
this product in production, we will also

01:02:59.700 --> 01:03:02.460
consider it on the example.

01:03:02.580 --> 01:03:04.960
The fourth factor is the cost of producers.

01:03:05.580 --> 01:03:07.560
The fifth factor is state taxes

01:03:07.560 --> 01:03:08.600
and subsidies.

01:03:08.860 --> 01:03:10.220
The sixth producer.

01:03:10.280 --> 01:03:11.520
The Seventh Goal.

01:03:11.700 --> 01:03:13.400
The 8th natural condition.

01:03:13.460 --> 01:03:16.220
The ninth is the expectation of the producers.

01:03:17.100 --> 01:03:17.800
Well let us.

01:03:18.640 --> 01:03:20.260
We talked about the factors of

01:03:20.260 --> 01:03:22.480
supply, now we talk about the

01:03:22.480 --> 01:03:24.360
factors of demand.

01:03:24.360 --> 01:03:28.220
The first factor of the offer is the price

01:03:28.220 --> 01:03:30.360
of the product.

01:03:31.380 --> 01:03:34.820
This is what economists call

01:03:34.820 --> 01:03:37.980
the law of proposition.

01:03:39.600 --> 01:03:41.620
Here it is, on the next slide.

01:03:43.100 --> 01:03:44.620
The Law of Proposal.

01:03:44.900 --> 01:03:48.860
The higher the price of the product,

01:03:48.860 --> 01:03:51.040
the more the producers

01:03:51.040 --> 01:03:55.300
want to sell during this

01:03:55.300 --> 01:03:58.060
time and under other unchanged

01:03:58.060 --> 01:04:00.560
conditions.

01:04:00.780 --> 01:04:03.600
This law is contrary

01:04:03.600 --> 01:04:05.840
to the law of demand.

01:04:05.880 --> 01:04:07.480
How did the law of demand sound?

01:04:07.840 --> 01:04:12.560
The lower the price, the more they want to buy.

01:04:13.000 --> 01:04:15.220
What is the proposal law?

01:04:17.360 --> 01:04:22.420
The higher the price, the more they want to sell.

01:04:23.240 --> 01:04:26.740
We have graphically introduced this law.

01:04:27.420 --> 01:04:30.720
Again, we are putting X on what?

01:04:31.380 --> 01:04:33.320
quantity of goods.

01:04:33.540 --> 01:04:34.980
But now it is no longer the size

01:04:34.980 --> 01:04:36.720
of demand, but the size of supply.

01:04:37.300 --> 01:04:39.960
And again, the price of the goods.

01:04:41.200 --> 01:04:42.080
And what do we see?

01:04:42.160 --> 01:04:44.560
The rising function.

01:04:47.740 --> 01:04:53.300
The higher the price of the goods,

01:04:53.300 --> 01:04:57.120
the more they want to produce and

01:04:57.120 --> 01:04:58.660
sell.

01:04:59.520 --> 01:05:00.700
Why is it so?

01:05:01.320 --> 01:05:05.940
Let us look at this on a simple

01:05:05.940 --> 01:05:08.840
conditional example.

01:05:08.840 --> 01:05:11.600
Let us take a very conditional

01:05:11.600 --> 01:05:13.860
example with you.

