We increase output, we increase all

01:57:57.590 --> 01:58:00.350
factors, sorry, n times, that is,

01:58:00.350 --> 01:58:01.230
labor, if capital has increased

01:58:01.230 --> 01:58:03.250
n times twice, in my example,

01:58:03.250 --> 01:58:05.590
and output increases

01:58:05.590 --> 01:58:08.230
less than n times, for example,

01:58:08.230 --> 01:58:10.310
one and a half times.

01:58:10.690 --> 01:58:13.350
Then we say that there is a decreasing

01:58:13.350 --> 01:58:16.390
return on scale.

01:58:16.650 --> 01:58:17.710
And the third case.

01:58:18.390 --> 01:58:21.090
We increased both factors, all

01:58:21.090 --> 01:58:24.550
factors increased n times twice

01:58:24.550 --> 01:58:26.790
in my example, and the output

01:58:26.790 --> 01:58:28.810
increased also n times, too

01:58:28.810 --> 01:58:29.450
twice.

01:58:30.210 --> 01:58:33.670
Then we say that there is a

01:58:33.670 --> 01:58:36.890
constant return on scale.

01:58:37.030 --> 01:58:39.290
The nature of the return on scale,

01:58:39.290 --> 01:58:42.230
it plays a very important role in

01:58:42.230 --> 01:58:45.570
determining the optimal size of the enterprise.

01:58:45.870 --> 01:58:46.830
Let me say, the giraffes.

01:58:48.230 --> 01:58:51.090
They can be collected in a small workshop.

01:58:52.190 --> 01:58:54.430
Maybe of course.

01:58:54.950 --> 01:58:57.610
The car, as a production complex,

01:58:57.610 --> 01:59:00.610
in terms of labor and capital, we

01:59:00.610 --> 01:59:03.490
may suppose, is a hundred times greater

01:59:03.490 --> 01:59:06.370
than such a small workshop.

01:59:07.550 --> 01:59:11.210
That is, it uses a hundred times more

01:59:11.210 --> 01:59:12.770
of the factors of production.

01:59:12.870 --> 01:59:16.090
And the output of the car car

01:59:16.090 --> 01:59:19.030
is increased by 200 or 300 times.

01:59:19.530 --> 01:59:21.290
What does that mean?

01:59:22.610 --> 01:59:25.650
As a car, assembling cars in a large

01:59:25.650 --> 01:59:29.310
factory is more effective than in

01:59:29.310 --> 01:59:30.230
a small workshop.

01:59:31.050 --> 01:59:32.630
So if the return on scale increases,

01:59:32.630 --> 01:59:34.530
what do we have?

01:59:42.250 --> 01:59:44.230
Increase the size of the enterprise.

01:59:44.330 --> 01:59:45.110
Another example.

01:59:45.210 --> 01:59:47.490
In Soviet times, they were

01:59:47.490 --> 01:59:48.890
very interested in building

01:59:49.090 --> 01:59:50.950
giant enterprises, including

01:59:50.950 --> 01:59:52.490
in agriculture.

01:59:53.310 --> 01:59:55.950
They built, for example, giant pig

01:59:55.950 --> 01:59:59.690
farms for thousands or even tens

01:59:59.690 --> 02:00:01.870
of thousands of cattle.

02:00:02.570 --> 02:00:04.290
Not only that the whole ecology flew within

02:00:04.290 --> 02:00:05.630
a radius of 100 kilometers.

02:00:06.290 --> 02:00:07.510
Here is what was.

02:00:08.150 --> 02:00:10.570
For example, a giant pig farm

02:00:10.570 --> 02:00:14.870
uses a hundred times more factor

02:00:14.870 --> 02:00:17.430
production than a small farm.

02:00:18.690 --> 02:00:21.090
And the meat production

02:00:21.090 --> 02:00:23.310
in her is, let’s say, only ten

02:00:23.310 --> 02:00:24.270
times more.

02:00:25.370 --> 02:00:27.090
What does that mean?

02:00:27.790 --> 02:00:29.550
That large enterprises in agriculture

02:00:29.550 --> 02:00:31.950
are economically inefficient.

02:00:32.190 --> 02:00:33.750
This is why small farms

02:00:33.750 --> 02:00:36.490
are quite effective in agriculture.

