02:00:39.010 --> 02:00:42.890
And when we increase the size of the

02:00:42.890 --> 02:00:46.050
enterprise, we sooner or later come

02:00:46.050 --> 02:00:48.590
to a situation in which the increasing

02:00:48.590 --> 02:00:51.050
return on scale is replaced

02:00:51.050 --> 02:00:53.590
by a constant, and then decreasing.

02:00:54.350 --> 02:00:56.890
This means that it is not worth strengthening

02:00:56.890 --> 02:00:59.710
the company.

02:01:01.270 --> 02:01:03.810
It is better to enjoy a large

02:01:03.810 --> 02:01:04.910
number of, but a smaller

02:01:04.910 --> 02:01:06.530
size.

02:01:06.630 --> 02:01:10.710
Knowing the production function, we

02:01:10.710 --> 02:01:14.990
can always calculate the cost of the company.

02:01:15.170 --> 02:01:17.750
Here we move to the second question.

02:01:27.610 --> 02:01:30.590
Economists divide costs into

02:01:30.590 --> 02:01:33.090
accounting and economic.

02:01:33.190 --> 02:01:34.810
Definition of accounting costs.

02:01:34.890 --> 02:01:36.470
Please look at the slide.

02:01:37.970 --> 02:01:40.970
Accounting costs of a company are

02:01:40.970 --> 02:01:46.560
the amount of actual payments purchased

02:01:46.700 --> 02:01:48.640
by resources.

02:01:48.740 --> 02:01:49.920
Well, that is very easy.

02:01:50.840 --> 02:01:55.370
To produce something, a company

02:01:55.370 --> 02:01:59.170
needs a variety of resources.

02:01:59.790 --> 02:02:02.790
This company purchases.

02:02:02.890 --> 02:02:06.270
A accountant then summarizes all these

02:02:06.270 --> 02:02:07.470
payments purchased by resources

02:02:07.470 --> 02:02:11.570
and enters them into its accounting

02:02:11.570 --> 02:02:13.930
report.

02:02:15.390 --> 02:02:20.510
Let us look at the simplest

02:02:20.510 --> 02:02:22.230
example.

02:02:22.330 --> 02:02:24.730
Let us look at the simplest

02:02:24.730 --> 02:02:28.330
example of accounting costs.

02:02:29.430 --> 02:02:32.630
Suppose the company uses equipment

02:02:32.630 --> 02:02:37.950
worth 200 rubles and a service

02:02:37.950 --> 02:02:40.930
life, say, 5 years.

02:02:41.750 --> 02:02:43.890
The entire cost of the equipment

02:02:43.890 --> 02:02:45.950
cannot be attributed to the

02:02:45.950 --> 02:02:47.050
cost of one year.

02:02:47.910 --> 02:02:50.230
We need to use amortization.

02:02:50.790 --> 02:02:53.030
When using the simplest linear

02:02:53.030 --> 02:02:55.890
depreciation, the cost of one

02:02:55.890 --> 02:02:58.270
year will be attributed, respectively,

02:02:58.270 --> 02:03:00.750
200, divided by 5, 40

02:03:00.750 --> 02:03:02.550
rubles.

02:03:03.230 --> 02:03:13.050
The accountant makes its report.

02:03:13.370 --> 02:03:16.950
The amortisation is 40 rubles.

02:03:17.050 --> 02:03:21.530
Further, let’s say, a firm uses an

02:03:21.630 --> 02:03:27.070
annual accountant writing 80 raw materials

02:03:27.070 --> 02:03:32.130
and paying a firm, let’s say, 60

02:03:32.130 --> 02:03:46.330
rubles of salary per year.

02:03:46.330 --> 02:03:52.550
The accountant says, salary 60.

02:03:52.650 --> 02:03:54.370
Now let’s say that

02:03:54.470 --> 02:03:57.950
the equipment is 20 rubles.

02:03:59.430 --> 02:04:01.610
The annual loan

02:04:01.610 --> 02:04:04.390
rate is 20 rubles.

02:04:05.870 --> 02:04:08.550
The loan fee is 20 rubles.

02:04:09.630 --> 02:04:12.790
Suppose that no more payments are

02:04:12.790 --> 02:04:15.490
made by the company.

02:04:16.250 --> 02:04:18.590
Well, it does not incur administrative,

02:04:18.850 --> 02:04:20.730
transportation, advertising, research,

02:04:21.030 --> 02:04:23.110
does not pay taxes and is not

02:04:23.110 --> 02:04:24.490
attributable to cost.

02:04:24.970 --> 02:04:27.090
Nothing of that.

02:04:28.470 --> 02:04:30.570
The accountant summarizes all these

02:04:30.570 --> 02:04:32.230
payments and writes.

02:04:36.510 --> 02:04:38.590
The accounting costs amounted

02:04:38.590 --> 02:04:41.550
to 200 rubles.

02:04:41.650 --> 02:04:45.510
The economist has a little of his own view.

02:04:51.460 --> 02:04:54.260
Alternative costs are

02:04:54.260 --> 02:04:56.920
economic costs.

02:04:56.920 --> 02:05:00.220
They represent the value of

02:05:00.220 --> 02:05:03.320
the goods that could be obtained

02:05:03.320 --> 02:05:08.060
by the most profitable of

02:05:08.060 --> 02:05:13.250
all alternative ways of

02:05:13.250 --> 02:05:15.930
using limited resources.

02:05:16.030 --> 02:05:18.450
I am afraid it is not very clear, but it can be easier.

02:05:18.450 --> 02:05:21.930
In practical calculations,

02:05:21.930 --> 02:05:25.650
economic costs include, in addition

02:05:25.650 --> 02:05:29.430
to the explicit or accounting

02:05:29.430 --> 02:05:33.210
costs, also the implicit

02:05:33.210 --> 02:05:35.190
costs.

02:05:35.210 --> 02:05:37.650
Can we write that economic

02:05:37.650 --> 02:05:42.550
costs are equal to what?

02:05:42.710 --> 02:05:46.050
Accounting costs plus some other

02:05:46.050 --> 02:05:48.930
unclear costs.

02:05:50.370 --> 02:05:56.750
What is accounting costs?

02:05:56.850 --> 02:05:57.850
I have already said.

02:05:59.170 --> 02:06:01.830
It is not clear what implicit costs are.

02:06:01.930 --> 02:06:02.850
We read.

02:06:03.950 --> 02:06:07.750
The implicit costs are the

02:06:07.750 --> 02:06:11.410
amount of incomes of the

02:06:11.410 --> 02:06:16.050
company on its own resources.

02:06:16.530 --> 02:06:19.910
It is about the income that the

02:06:19.910 --> 02:06:23.550
management of the company could

02:06:23.550 --> 02:06:32.590
get by using its resources not in

02:06:32.590 --> 02:06:37.170
this business, but somehow differently.

02:06:37.270 --> 02:06:39.710
Let us find out.

02:06:39.810 --> 02:06:44.880
Imagine that you have started your own

02:06:44.880 --> 02:06:45.580
business.

02:06:45.680 --> 02:06:47.740
You come into this business not

02:06:47.740 --> 02:06:49.140
with empty hands.

02:06:49.600 --> 02:06:55.090
What did you bring with you?

02:06:55.190 --> 02:06:58.190
Maybe a lot of

02:06:58.190 --> 02:07:00.290
money.

02:07:01.330 --> 02:07:06.890
Let’s say 100 rubles.

02:07:06.990 --> 02:07:08.950
Could you use this

02:07:08.950 --> 02:07:11.890
capital as an alternative?

02:07:11.990 --> 02:07:16.490
Of course could.

02:07:16.590 --> 02:07:18.490
What is the easiest way

02:07:18.490 --> 02:07:19.550
to use that money?

02:07:19.650 --> 02:07:24.150
You could put them in the bank.

02:07:25.520 --> 02:07:27.400
You would get a percentage.

02:07:27.500 --> 02:07:29.520
If you invest that money in your

02:07:31.940 --> 02:07:36.760
own company, you have lost that percentage.

02:07:36.860 --> 02:07:41.960
And this unreceived percentage will

02:07:41.960 --> 02:07:48.430
enter the firm's implicit costs.

02:07:48.530 --> 02:07:51.250
Well, let’s say you invested 100

02:07:51.250 --> 02:07:52.930
rubles in your business.

02:07:53.750 --> 02:07:56.290
You had to close your

02:07:56.290 --> 02:07:58.890
bank account.

02:07:58.890 --> 02:08:04.170
You have lost 10% of your invested

02:08:04.170 --> 02:08:04.830
money.

02:08:18.650 --> 02:08:20.450
I for simplicity assume that the

02:08:20.450 --> 02:08:23.530
bank pays on deposits also 10%.

02:08:23.530 --> 02:08:28.980
So, the implicit cost that these

02:08:28.980 --> 02:08:30.300
funds you got as if free, but

02:08:30.300 --> 02:08:32.700
that does not mean that their

02:08:32.700 --> 02:08:35.100
use should be taken into account.

02:08:35.520 --> 02:08:37.540
So you invested 100 rubles,

02:08:37.900 --> 02:08:41.160
lost 10% on those funds, which

02:08:41.420 --> 02:08:42.880
you could get if you kept that

02:08:42.880 --> 02:08:44.320
money in the bank.

02:08:44.860 --> 02:08:46.420
And accordingly, in the implicit

02:08:46.420 --> 02:08:48.200
costs will include this unreceived

02:08:48.200 --> 02:08:49.800
percentage of 10 rubles.

02:08:51.020 --> 02:08:52.360
and further.

02:08:53.160 --> 02:08:54.620
In order to start your business,

02:08:54.620 --> 02:08:59.540
you had to leave your job.

02:09:00.620 --> 02:09:02.880
You probably worked for hiring before.

02:09:03.500 --> 02:09:04.680
So you lost?

02:09:06.280 --> 02:09:07.820
The wage.

02:09:08.360 --> 02:09:12.520
Unreceived wages will also be included

02:09:12.520 --> 02:09:15.360
in the firm’s implicit costs.

02:09:16.180 --> 02:09:19.080
Let’s say, by hiring, you

02:09:19.080 --> 02:09:20.620
earned 200 rubles.

02:09:21.080 --> 02:09:24.140
When you start your business, you lose

02:09:24.200 --> 02:09:25.640
those 200 rubles.

02:09:25.880 --> 02:09:27.840
These 200 rubles of unreceived

02:09:27.840 --> 02:09:30.280
salary economists include in the implicit

02:09:30.280 --> 02:09:33.420
costs of your company.

02:09:33.760 --> 02:09:35.820
I write.

02:09:35.820 --> 02:09:41.540
Unpaid salary.

02:09:42.700 --> 02:09:43.420
How many were there?

02:09:43.460 --> 02:09:45.640
20 rubles, I would say.

02:09:45.900 --> 02:09:47.860
Unpaid salary.

02:09:48.280 --> 02:09:50.840
Another assumption.

02:09:51.160 --> 02:09:53.440
Suppose for your business, you have turned

02:09:53.440 --> 02:10:11.430
your apartment into an office or a

02:10:11.430 --> 02:10:12.010
warehouse.

02:10:12.110 --> 02:10:13.670
What did you lose in this case?

02:10:14.350 --> 02:10:15.630
How do you estimate your losses?

02:10:15.730 --> 02:10:20.100
You could provide this apartment

02:10:20.100 --> 02:10:22.240
for your business, you lost

02:10:22.240 --> 02:10:24.480
those 20 rubles.

02:10:24.980 --> 02:10:31.820
So, the unreceived rent is

02:10:31.820 --> 02:10:34.580
also legally included in the implicit

02:10:34.580 --> 02:10:36.960
costs.

02:10:37.060 --> 02:10:40.380
Unreceived rent is 20 rubles.

02:10:41.680 --> 02:10:42.780
Well well well.

02:10:43.320 --> 02:10:46.120
Summarizing all these lost income,

02:10:46.120 --> 02:10:55.240
we get the implicit costs of the company.

02:10:56.520 --> 02:10:59.900
We got 50 rubles.

02:11:01.220 --> 02:11:03.940
It turns out that the total

02:11:03.940 --> 02:11:06.480
economic costs of the company

02:11:06.480 --> 02:11:09.140
are accounting costs of 200, implicit

02:11:09.140 --> 02:11:16.020
costs of 50, and that 250

02:11:16.020 --> 02:11:18.000
rubles.

02:11:18.100 --> 02:11:19.700
But now we have to answer the most

02:11:19.700 --> 02:11:21.100
important question.

02:11:22.180 --> 02:11:24.040
Why are economists original?

02:11:25.040 --> 02:11:27.600
For what reason they have invented

02:11:27.600 --> 02:11:29.780
in addition to the explicit

02:11:29.780 --> 02:11:31.660
or accounting costs, which are

02:11:31.660 --> 02:11:34.220
obvious to all, some implicit

02:11:34.220 --> 02:11:36.800
costs, which, I will repeat,

02:11:36.800 --> 02:11:40.240
the firm does not even pay anyone.

02:11:42.130 --> 02:11:46.810
The implicit costs are those income that

02:11:47.390 --> 02:11:51.050
entrepreneurs have lost by investing their

02:11:52.370 --> 02:11:55.490
resources in the company, which they have provided

02:11:55.490 --> 02:11:58.950
to the company, supposedly free of charge.

02:12:00.010 --> 02:12:00.810
Here is why.

02:12:02.030 --> 02:12:05.710
Without knowing the implicit

02:12:05.710 --> 02:12:09.070
costs, we cannot estimate how

02:12:09.070 --> 02:12:13.030
profitable a business is.

02:12:13.850 --> 02:12:15.290
I have already said about the costs.

02:12:15.930 --> 02:12:18.230
The total economic costs amounted

02:12:18.410 --> 02:12:22.870
to 250 rubles, but after all,

02:12:22.870 --> 02:12:25.610
the firm produces something

02:12:25.610 --> 02:12:28.890
and, suppose, produces, sells

02:12:28.890 --> 02:12:32.030
products and, suppose, the

02:12:32.030 --> 02:12:37.150
annual revenue of the

02:12:38.190 --> 02:12:43.090
firm is, suppose, 240 rubles.

02:12:52.800 --> 02:12:54.920
How to assess the accountant situation?

02:12:55.020 --> 02:12:56.820
The accountant only takes account

02:12:56.820 --> 02:12:58.800
of the accounting costs.

02:12:58.860 --> 02:13:00.940
Not because he is so stupid,

02:13:00.940 --> 02:13:03.340
but because the accountant guides

02:13:03.340 --> 02:13:05.080
certain rules of

02:13:05.080 --> 02:13:06.760
accounting.

02:13:08.260 --> 02:13:10.420
The accountant will most likely congratulate

02:13:10.420 --> 02:13:13.280
you on the profit.

02:13:13.280 --> 02:13:18.100
Revenue 240, accounting expenses 200.

02:13:18.780 --> 02:13:34.560
The profit was 40 rubles.

02:13:34.660 --> 02:13:36.980
How do you assess the situation of an economist?

02:13:37.080 --> 02:13:42.660
The economist is losing.

02:13:42.760 --> 02:13:49.840
Revenue minus economic costs.

02:13:49.840 --> 02:13:53.180
It was minus 10.

02:13:54.220 --> 02:13:55.580
Loss of 10 rubles.

02:13:57.140 --> 02:14:00.140
What does this mean in the mouth of an economist?

02:14:00.960 --> 02:14:02.040
And very simple.

02:14:02.920 --> 02:14:04.620
No one has pulled you into this business.

02:14:05.760 --> 02:14:09.240
If you didn’t go, how much money

02:14:09.640 --> 02:14:12.100
would you have in your wallet

02:14:12.100 --> 02:14:14.100
at the end of the year?

02:14:15.500 --> 02:14:18.180
You would keep your money in the bank.

02:14:18.400 --> 02:14:20.680
You would have a annual interest rate of 10 rubles.

02:14:21.320 --> 02:14:23.080
They would hire themselves.

02:14:23.300 --> 02:14:25.560
Annual salary is 20 rubles.

02:14:26.040 --> 02:14:27.520
The apartment could be rented.

02:14:27.800 --> 02:14:29.380
The rent would be paid 20 rubles

02:14:29.380 --> 02:14:30.140
per year.

02:14:30.560 --> 02:14:32.040
You would have 50 rubles

02:14:32.040 --> 02:14:34.480
in your pocket.

02:14:35.320 --> 02:14:37.300
How much do you have in your pocket

02:14:37.300 --> 02:14:37.840
for the year?

02:14:38.760 --> 02:14:41.540
Only 40 rubles of accounting profit.

02:14:41.860 --> 02:14:44.660
Profit for 240.

02:14:44.760 --> 02:14:46.500
Accountant with 200.

02:14:46.800 --> 02:14:48.160
So you have taxes in your

02:14:48.160 --> 02:14:48.700
pocket.

02:14:48.700 --> 02:14:49.560
I don’t take, of course.

02:14:50.120 --> 02:14:51.120
40 rubles

02:14:52.140 --> 02:14:55.280
So you just do not have a profitable

02:14:55.280 --> 02:14:58.380
business under these conditions.

02:14:58.380 --> 02:15:04.580
Now let us summarize.

02:15:05.780 --> 02:15:07.840
Look at the slide.

02:15:07.960 --> 02:15:10.900
The difference between revenue

02:15:10.900 --> 02:15:13.000
and accounting costs is

02:15:13.000 --> 02:15:16.580
the accounting profit of the company.

02:15:16.780 --> 02:15:18.200
We have counted.

02:15:19.460 --> 02:15:20.780
Revenue minus accounting

02:15:20.780 --> 02:15:23.320
costs and accounting profit.

02:15:23.320 --> 02:15:26.080
The difference between revenue

02:15:26.080 --> 02:15:29.760
and economic costs is the

02:15:29.760 --> 02:15:32.080
economic profit or surplus profit

02:15:32.080 --> 02:15:34.700
of the company.

02:15:34.960 --> 02:15:37.640
This is the economic profit,

02:15:37.660 --> 02:15:40.140
the revenue minus the

02:15:40.140 --> 02:15:43.440
economic costs.

02:15:43.840 --> 02:15:45.860
And the third conclusion we can make.

02:15:46.620 --> 02:15:49.300
If the profit is negative,

02:15:49.300 --> 02:15:52.680
the company has a loss.

02:15:52.980 --> 02:15:55.680
Business is not beneficial to entrepreneurs.

