his practical activity.

02:23:56.830 --> 02:24:00.970
We start with the third question, the types of costs.

02:24:03.290 --> 02:24:06.090
All costs, both accounting and

02:24:06.630 --> 02:24:09.430
complete economic, can be divided

02:24:09.430 --> 02:24:13.790
into constant and variable.

02:24:15.850 --> 02:24:18.010
What is at the basis of this division?

02:24:18.330 --> 02:24:20.050
See here.

02:24:20.730 --> 02:24:24.010
The company is increasing the production.

02:24:26.980 --> 02:24:30.860
And it is evident that with the increase of

02:24:30.860 --> 02:24:35.600
output, some costs change, while

02:24:35.600 --> 02:24:36.920
others remain unchanged.

02:24:37.340 --> 02:24:41.260
The costs that do not change with

02:24:41.260 --> 02:24:44.880
the increase in output are

02:24:44.880 --> 02:24:47.020
called fixed costs.

02:24:47.020 --> 02:24:50.560
The costs that change with the

02:24:50.560 --> 02:24:53.860
increase in output are called

02:24:53.860 --> 02:24:56.020
variable costs.

02:24:56.120 --> 02:24:59.020
Why are costs divided into constant

02:24:59.020 --> 02:25:00.720
and variable?

02:25:02.240 --> 02:25:05.540
Because we also divide the factors of

02:25:05.540 --> 02:25:09.080
production into constant and variable.

02:25:09.440 --> 02:25:12.620
The fact is that some factors

02:25:12.620 --> 02:25:16.060
of production can be changed easily

02:25:16.060 --> 02:25:18.500
and quickly with an increase

02:25:18.500 --> 02:25:19.540
in output.

02:25:19.720 --> 02:25:20.860
To increase the issue.

02:25:22.220 --> 02:25:24.500
Well, let’s say, it’s quite easy to hire

02:25:24.500 --> 02:25:27.020
new employees in the company.

02:25:28.400 --> 02:25:30.360
Workers are a variable factor

02:25:30.360 --> 02:25:31.480
of production.

02:25:31.480 --> 02:25:34.460
But the company takes a certain

02:25:34.460 --> 02:25:37.340
amount of time to purchase

02:25:37.340 --> 02:25:39.560
new equipment, that is, to use

02:25:39.560 --> 02:25:41.840
additional capital.

02:25:42.320 --> 02:25:44.200
Therefore, we usually refer equipment

02:25:44.200 --> 02:25:47.260
to a constant factor of production

02:25:47.260 --> 02:25:50.200
in a short period of time.

02:25:51.660 --> 02:25:54.460
Look at the definition again on the

02:25:54.460 --> 02:25:55.640
slide.

02:25:56.460 --> 02:25:59.340
Fixed costs are costs that

02:25:59.400 --> 02:26:02.180
do not change with the

02:26:02.180 --> 02:26:04.260
change in output.

02:26:05.000 --> 02:26:07.820
This is the cost of constant factors

02:26:07.820 --> 02:26:09.200
of production.

02:26:10.360 --> 02:26:12.400
Usually, the fixed costs

02:26:12.400 --> 02:26:15.040
include depreciation, rent,

02:26:15.040 --> 02:26:17.080
interest on the loan,

02:26:17.880 --> 02:26:19.520
and management salary.

02:26:20.040 --> 02:26:21.620
Unclear costs are also

02:26:21.620 --> 02:26:23.300
usually fixed.

02:26:24.520 --> 02:26:27.200
Now the variable costs again.

02:26:27.460 --> 02:26:29.600
Variable costs are costs whose

02:26:29.660 --> 02:26:32.320
value changes with the change

02:26:32.320 --> 02:26:33.320
in output.

02:26:33.960 --> 02:26:36.440
This is the cost of variable factors

02:26:36.440 --> 02:26:37.640
of production.

02:26:38.700 --> 02:26:40.800
These usually include wages in workers'

02:26:40.800 --> 02:26:42.720
production, raw materials and

02:26:43.280 --> 02:26:45.180
materials costs, electricity

02:26:45.600 --> 02:26:47.280
for technological purposes

02:26:47.280 --> 02:26:49.060
and others.

02:26:52.810 --> 02:26:56.490
Fixed costs and variable

02:26:56.490 --> 02:26:58.750
costs.

02:27:02.150 --> 02:27:04.450
If we summarize them, we

02:27:04.450 --> 02:27:07.530
get the total cost.

