Average variable cost, AVC,

02:28:03.890 --> 02:28:05.730
is the variable cost

02:28:05.850 --> 02:28:07.690
per unit of production.

02:28:08.690 --> 02:28:09.850
How to count them?

02:28:10.390 --> 02:28:13.250
We divide the total amount of variable costs

02:28:13.250 --> 02:28:14.910
by the volume of production.

02:28:15.070 --> 02:28:16.790
Look at the formula.

02:28:17.490 --> 02:28:21.590
And finally, the average

02:28:21.590 --> 02:28:25.830
total cost is the total cost

02:28:25.910 --> 02:28:27.930
per unit of production.

02:28:29.850 --> 02:28:30.790
How to calculate?

02:28:31.730 --> 02:28:33.630
Total cost, TC, can

02:28:33.630 --> 02:28:36.130
be divided by

02:28:36.130 --> 02:28:36.870
Q.

02:28:37.930 --> 02:28:39.670
Or else can be counted.

02:28:40.150 --> 02:28:42.450
Average constant and variable

02:28:42.450 --> 02:28:45.750
costs can be summed up.

02:28:49.340 --> 02:28:52.860
A very important role in economic

02:28:52.860 --> 02:28:57.080
analysis is played by marginal

02:28:57.300 --> 02:28:58.360
cost.

02:28:59.480 --> 02:29:02.180
Limit costs are the increase

02:29:02.180 --> 02:29:05.480
in total costs when the output

02:29:05.480 --> 02:29:08.540
increases by one unit.

