02:34:20.550 --> 02:34:23.390
is a period during

02:34:23.390 --> 02:34:26.310
which some factors

02:34:26.310 --> 02:34:29.830
of production cannot be

02:34:29.830 --> 02:34:33.230
changed and others can

02:34:33.230 --> 02:34:35.310
be changed.

02:34:38.010 --> 02:34:40.350
Capital is considered to be a constant

02:34:40.350 --> 02:34:43.410
factor of production, and labour is

02:34:43.410 --> 02:34:45.690
considered to be a variable factor.

02:34:47.780 --> 02:34:52.440
Accordingly, capital costs in the

02:34:52.440 --> 02:34:54.140
short period are fixed costs,

02:34:54.140 --> 02:34:57.500
and labor costs in the short

02:34:57.500 --> 02:35:00.240
period are variable costs.

02:35:03.230 --> 02:35:05.790
Let’s see what the costs

02:35:05.790 --> 02:35:09.310
can be in the short term.

02:35:10.250 --> 02:35:13.190
Let’s start with the constant cost.

02:35:14.070 --> 02:35:18.030
Look at the slide again.

02:35:18.470 --> 02:35:21.130
Fixed costs are those costs

02:35:21.130 --> 02:35:24.470
that do not change with the change

02:35:24.470 --> 02:35:27.950
in the volume of the output.

02:35:28.210 --> 02:35:29.010
See also.

02:35:29.890 --> 02:35:31.950
The issue changes on the left chart,

02:35:32.970 --> 02:35:36.130
and the fixed costs do not change.

02:35:36.310 --> 02:35:39.250
Accordingly, the function of constant costs

02:35:39.250 --> 02:35:41.990
is a straight line of the

02:35:41.990 --> 02:35:43.610
parallel axis x.

02:35:47.080 --> 02:35:50.000
Now let’s talk about the function of average

02:35:50.000 --> 02:35:51.060
constant costs.

