02:51:21.630 --> 02:51:24.920
from zero to five, the limit costs

02:51:24.930 --> 02:51:28.180
are constantly decreasing, eventually

02:51:28.190 --> 02:51:30.300
reaching a value of 16.

02:51:31.740 --> 02:51:34.800
After that, starting with issue

02:51:34.810 --> 02:51:36.700
6 and so on, the limit costs

02:51:36.710 --> 02:51:39.220
begin to rise.

02:51:39.820 --> 02:51:42.120
The average and fixed costs are always

02:51:42.130 --> 02:51:43.120
decreasing.

02:51:43.580 --> 02:51:44.920
There is nothing new here.

02:51:46.580 --> 02:51:49.660
The functions of the average variable

02:51:49.670 --> 02:51:52.900
and average total costs change

02:51:52.910 --> 02:51:53.920
immediately.

02:51:55.880 --> 02:51:58.500
Look what they will be now.

02:52:03.550 --> 02:52:05.250
Here is the slide.

02:52:06.670 --> 02:52:11.570
Limit and average costs.

02:52:11.580 --> 02:52:14.530
Look at what happens with

02:52:14.540 --> 02:52:16.270
the limit costs.

02:52:17.800 --> 02:52:19.380
As I said, first they decrease,

02:52:19.390 --> 02:52:22.520
then they reach the minimum, then

02:52:22.530 --> 02:52:25.480
they begin to strive, then they increase.

02:52:26.440 --> 02:52:28.820
What happens to the average

02:52:28.830 --> 02:52:30.640
variable cost?

02:52:31.620 --> 02:52:33.220
They first fall.

02:52:34.480 --> 02:52:36.320
But they are declining, as you

02:52:36.600 --> 02:52:40.020
can see, slower than the limit costs.

02:52:40.200 --> 02:52:41.040
Then look at.

02:52:41.300 --> 02:52:45.320
Within a certain period of time, the

02:52:45.330 --> 02:52:48.300
limit costs are already increasing.

02:52:49.700 --> 02:52:52.880
And the average variable costs,

02:52:55.750 --> 02:52:57.980
look carefully, they are still decreasing.

02:53:00.360 --> 02:53:03.620
And note that the average variable

02:53:03.630 --> 02:53:07.380
costs decrease until they

02:53:07.390 --> 02:53:10.840
are even above the limit costs.

02:53:12.540 --> 02:53:13.820
Hence the most important conclusion.

02:53:15.300 --> 02:53:18.900
The average variable cost

02:53:18.910 --> 02:53:21.800
reaches its minimum at

02:53:21.810 --> 02:53:26.660
the point where it is equal to

02:53:26.670 --> 02:53:28.340
the limit cost.

02:53:32.240 --> 02:53:36.080
Finally, let’s look at the average

02:53:36.090 --> 02:53:37.880
total cost function.

02:53:41.960 --> 02:53:44.260
This function comes out of infinity.

02:53:44.780 --> 02:53:47.120
For an infinite small quantity,

02:53:47.130 --> 02:53:49.500
the average total cost is very large

02:53:49.510 --> 02:53:51.760
because the output is very small.

02:53:53.420 --> 02:53:54.100
Next What?

02:53:55.040 --> 02:53:59.060
They decline and also necessarily

02:53:59.070 --> 02:54:02.780
reach their minimum at the point where

02:54:02.840 --> 02:54:06.860
they are equal to the limit costs.

02:54:07.260 --> 02:54:10.440
The function of the limit costs necessarily

02:54:10.450 --> 02:54:14.260
crosses the functions of the average

02:54:14.270 --> 02:54:16.680
variable and the average total

02:54:16.690 --> 02:54:21.000
cost at the points of their minimum.

02:54:24.300 --> 02:54:25.980
Once the minimum point is

02:54:25.990 --> 02:54:28.660
passed, the average total

02:54:28.670 --> 02:54:32.460
cost begins to rise.

02:54:32.660 --> 02:54:37.540
As they increase, they are constantly

02:54:37.550 --> 02:54:41.560
approaching the function of

02:54:41.570 --> 02:54:43.060
average variable costs.

02:54:44.900 --> 02:54:46.280
Think, why is it so?

02:54:49.120 --> 02:54:51.600
The average total cost is equal

02:54:51.610 --> 02:54:53.960
to what we have already mentioned,

02:55:00.700 --> 02:55:03.980
the average constant cost, plus

02:55:03.990 --> 02:55:07.680
the average variable cost.

02:55:07.920 --> 02:55:11.060
What are the average constant

02:55:11.070 --> 02:55:11.840
costs?

02:55:14.250 --> 02:55:14.850
to zero.

02:55:15.210 --> 02:55:16.390
I have said this many times.

02:55:17.290 --> 02:55:21.090
The average variable cost

02:55:21.100 --> 02:55:25.950
is the average total cost.

02:55:26.730 --> 02:55:29.650
Well, this is actually all about

02:55:29.660 --> 02:55:32.150
the fourth issue of this topic –

02:55:32.160 --> 02:55:33.810
the cost in the short term.

02:55:35.760 --> 02:55:38.180
There is another fifth issue on the subject

02:55:38.190 --> 02:55:40.200
– the costs in the long term.

02:55:40.900 --> 02:55:42.860
There will be nothing new there,

02:55:42.870 --> 02:55:45.980
except that I just want

02:55:45.990 --> 02:55:49.380
to emphasize that there

02:55:49.390 --> 02:55:53.640
are no constant costs in

02:55:53.650 --> 02:55:54.820
the long run.

02:55:56.100 --> 02:55:58.900
All costs are variable.

02:55:58.920 --> 02:55:59.420
Why is?

02:56:01.480 --> 02:56:05.960
Because in the long run, the company

02:56:05.970 --> 02:56:09.260
can change all the factors of production.

02:56:09.700 --> 02:56:10.880
She can find additional

02:56:10.890 --> 02:56:13.080
workers, she can install additional

02:56:13.090 --> 02:56:15.040
equipment, she can rent

02:56:15.050 --> 02:56:18.460
a more spacious

02:56:18.470 --> 02:56:19.800
building.

02:56:20.840 --> 02:56:22.500
All factors of production

02:56:22.510 --> 02:56:24.660
become variable, so all

02:56:24.670 --> 02:56:28.220
costs also become variable.

02:56:28.700 --> 02:56:32.540
There is no function of average

02:56:32.550 --> 02:56:33.580
constant cost.

02:56:34.140 --> 02:56:35.800
Is there only a function?

02:56:36.640 --> 02:56:39.480
The function of the limit costs is the function

02:56:39.490 --> 02:56:41.440
of the average cost.

02:56:42.280 --> 02:56:43.480
And it will be the same.

02:56:44.180 --> 02:56:46.120
The function of the limit costs first

02:56:46.130 --> 02:56:49.360
decreases, then reaches a minimum,

02:56:49.370 --> 02:56:52.080
then begins to increase.

02:56:52.340 --> 02:56:55.180
The average total cost function first

02:56:55.190 --> 02:56:58.180
decreases, then reaches the minimum

02:56:58.190 --> 02:57:00.300
at the point of intersection

02:57:00.310 --> 02:57:03.480
with the limit cost function.

02:57:04.140 --> 02:57:05.820
After that, the average total

02:57:05.830 --> 02:57:09.480
cost function begins to increase.

02:57:16.770 --> 02:57:19.670
Let us start with the fourth topic

02:57:19.680 --> 02:57:21.190
of our course.

02:57:22.110 --> 02:57:25.410
Market Structures and Company Behavior.

02:57:25.830 --> 02:57:28.990
Here we will talk about how the company

02:57:29.000 --> 02:57:31.090
operates in certain market

02:57:31.100 --> 02:57:32.690
conditions.

02:57:34.050 --> 02:57:35.950
And it is probably obvious

02:57:35.960 --> 02:57:39.090
that the behavior of a company depends

02:57:39.100 --> 02:57:41.010
not only on the amount of

02:57:41.020 --> 02:57:43.910
resources it has, but also on the

02:57:43.920 --> 02:57:46.750
market environment in which it operates.

02:57:47.430 --> 02:57:50.030
In other words, the behavior of the company

02:57:50.040 --> 02:57:51.810
depends on the type of market.

02:57:52.530 --> 02:57:54.710
Please look at the slide.

02:57:54.720 --> 02:57:56.890
The first question we will discuss

02:57:56.900 --> 02:57:58.930
with you is called “types of

02:57:58.940 --> 02:58:01.270
market structures”.

02:58:01.280 --> 02:58:04.690
Or it will be about types of markets.

02:58:06.560 --> 02:58:09.560
Please see, there is...

02:58:09.570 --> 02:58:12.020
Microeconomics distinguishes four types

02:58:12.030 --> 02:58:14.640
of market structures or forms of market

02:58:14.650 --> 02:58:16.320
organization.

02:58:16.740 --> 02:58:20.320
This is perfect competition,

02:58:20.900 --> 02:58:24.000
monopoly, oligopoly,

02:58:24.300 --> 02:58:26.320
monopolistic competition.

02:58:31.170 --> 02:58:33.730
Let’s start with perfect competition.

02:58:35.090 --> 02:58:37.350
Well, very often perfect

02:58:37.360 --> 02:58:39.750
competition is misunderstood.

02:58:40.110 --> 02:58:41.810
They think that perfect

02:58:41.820 --> 02:58:45.940
competition is something like

02:58:45.950 --> 02:58:48.460
absolutely harsh, ruthless

02:58:48.560 --> 02:58:50.140
competition.

02:58:50.200 --> 02:58:52.800
Actually nothing like that.

02:58:52.980 --> 02:58:55.140
The definition is very simple.

02:58:55.260 --> 02:58:58.420
Perfect competition is a market

02:58:58.430 --> 02:59:02.260
structure in which there are

02:59:02.270 --> 02:59:05.760
so many sellers and buyers that

02:59:05.770 --> 02:59:10.800
none of them can influence the

02:59:10.810 --> 02:59:13.760
market price by changing

02:59:13.770 --> 02:59:16.440
the volume of their

02:59:16.450 --> 02:59:18.700
supply or demand.

02:59:20.090 --> 02:59:21.990
The price of a product in a completely

02:59:22.000 --> 02:59:24.630
competitive market is determined by

02:59:24.640 --> 02:59:27.690
the interaction of thousands of independent

02:59:27.700 --> 02:59:31.810
buyers and hundreds of independent sellers.

02:59:32.290 --> 02:59:34.070
Every buyer and every seller

02:59:34.080 --> 02:59:36.890
is a piece of sand on the scale

02:59:36.900 --> 02:59:39.850
of the market, which can not change

02:59:39.860 --> 02:59:42.750
anything in the market by

02:59:42.760 --> 02:59:44.610
its behavior.

02:59:45.010 --> 02:59:48.650
Let’s look at the signs of

02:59:48.660 --> 02:59:50.310
perfect competition.

02:59:52.750 --> 02:59:54.850
Well, I actually said about the

02:59:54.860 --> 02:59:55.790
first sign.

02:59:55.870 --> 02:59:57.570
Here is a sign.

02:59:58.050 --> 02:59:59.630
Each of the very large numbers

02:59:59.640 --> 03:00:01.930
of sellers and buyers has such a

03:00:01.940 --> 03:00:04.530
small market share that they cannot

03:00:04.540 --> 03:00:06.690
change the market price by their

03:00:06.700 --> 03:00:09.930
behavior, but can sell or buy

03:00:09.940 --> 03:00:13.430
as many products as they want

03:00:13.440 --> 03:00:15.810
at that price.

03:00:19.200 --> 03:00:22.740
Let me give you an example, I think it

03:00:22.760 --> 03:00:24.780
will be appropriate.

03:00:25.220 --> 03:00:28.340
Here is a friend who lives

03:00:28.350 --> 03:00:31.160
in the Volgograd province, calls me in

03:00:31.170 --> 03:00:33.840
Moscow and asks what tomatoes in

03:00:33.850 --> 03:00:34.740
Moscow are for?

03:00:36.200 --> 03:00:38.900
The case was in the summer and not last

03:00:38.910 --> 03:00:42.180
year, I don’t remember what I answered,

03:00:42.360 --> 03:00:44.440
well, let’s say, 10 rubles per kilogram.

03:00:46.020 --> 03:00:48.060
She had an unfettered curiosity.

03:00:48.500 --> 03:00:51.400
She was going to bring a truck

03:00:51.410 --> 03:00:53.280
with Volga tomatoes to Moscow.

03:00:56.790 --> 03:00:58.390
So, what did she come from, having

03:00:58.530 --> 03:01:00.470
received my information, the price

03:01:00.480 --> 03:01:03.490
of tomatoes in Moscow 10 rubles per kilogram?

03:01:08.100 --> 03:01:11.140
It was based on the fact that

03:01:11.150 --> 03:01:13.000
if today the price is so, its appearance

03:01:13.760 --> 03:01:17.120
or not appearance on the

03:01:17.130 --> 03:01:21.140
market can not affect the price.

03:01:21.150 --> 03:01:26.870
But on the other hand, she is confident

03:01:27.250 --> 03:01:28.790
that since she holds a tiny

03:01:28.800 --> 03:01:30.850
share of the tomato market, she

03:01:30.860 --> 03:01:34.310
will be able to sell any quantity

03:01:34.320 --> 03:01:35.810
of her tomatoes at this price,

03:01:35.820 --> 03:01:37.290
10 rubles per kilogram.

03:01:38.820 --> 03:01:41.920
That is, and a ton, and three, and even

03:01:41.930 --> 03:01:44.000
five, and more, she just has no.

03:01:44.840 --> 03:01:47.100
It is clear that if she brought to

03:01:47.110 --> 03:01:49.740
Moscow at the same time, say,

03:01:49.750 --> 03:01:52.440
thousands of tons of tomatoes, then

03:01:52.450 --> 03:01:55.080
such a large seller would necessarily

03:01:55.090 --> 03:01:56.840
influence the market price.

03:01:57.440 --> 03:01:59.240
But that would no longer be a condition

03:01:59.250 --> 03:02:00.500
for perfect competition.

03:02:01.380 --> 03:02:03.780
Under perfect competition, market

03:02:03.790 --> 03:02:06.060
price is determined by the interaction

03:02:07.650 --> 03:02:10.230
of thousands of independent

03:02:10.240 --> 03:02:14.170
buyers, hundreds of independent

03:02:14.180 --> 03:02:16.690
sellers, each piece of

03:02:16.700 --> 03:02:19.930
sand on the general market

03:02:19.940 --> 03:02:22.550
scale, and no one alone

03:02:22.560 --> 03:02:24.330
can influence the price.

03:02:24.770 --> 03:02:26.910
Another example, so that it might

03:02:26.920 --> 03:02:28.410
be better understood.

03:02:29.530 --> 03:02:34.690
You encountered a neighbor at the entrance.

03:02:35.070 --> 03:02:37.870
He comes from the bazar.

03:02:38.930 --> 03:02:41.250
You ask him what tomatoes are for?

03:02:41.810 --> 03:02:45.550
He responds, 10 rubles per kilogram.

03:02:46.810 --> 03:02:49.170
So what are you coming from?

03:02:49.430 --> 03:02:51.850
How soon did that price come up?

03:02:52.910 --> 03:02:55.530
Your appearance or not appearing

03:02:55.540 --> 03:02:58.450
on the market as a buyer

03:02:58.460 --> 03:03:01.450
again can not affect the price.

03:03:02.090 --> 03:03:04.270
But you can buy at this price, for 10

03:03:04.280 --> 03:03:06.590
rubles, and a kilogram, and 3, and

03:03:06.600 --> 03:03:08.110
5, and even 10.

03:03:09.030 --> 03:03:11.430
That is, you also feel like

03:03:11.440 --> 03:03:13.390
a perfect competitor

03:03:13.400 --> 03:03:15.250
in the tomato market, but

03:03:15.260 --> 03:03:17.530
not as a seller, but as a buyer.

03:03:19.690 --> 03:03:21.830
Let’s look at the schedule.

03:03:24.660 --> 03:03:28.180
Balanced market price and demand curve

03:03:28.190 --> 03:03:30.620
for a product of a particular firm.

03:03:30.780 --> 03:03:33.120
Look at two schedules.

03:03:34.240 --> 03:03:37.260
The left chart illustrates the demand

03:03:37.270 --> 03:03:38.920
for supply in a completely

03:03:38.930 --> 03:03:40.360
competitive market.

03:03:40.780 --> 03:03:42.660
I repeat again.

03:03:42.900 --> 03:03:45.860
There are thousands of buyers and hundreds

03:03:45.870 --> 03:03:47.780
of independent sellers.

03:03:48.100 --> 03:03:52.000
On the X-axis we place the total

03:03:52.010 --> 03:03:54.080
number of tomatoes sold and purchased

03:03:54.090 --> 03:03:55.840
on this market.

03:03:56.240 --> 03:03:57.060
And what do we see?

03:03:58.020 --> 03:04:02.200
That at the price P with the star

03:04:02.210 --> 03:04:06.040
we have some market balance.

03:04:06.460 --> 03:04:08.420
Demand on the tomato market

03:04:08.430 --> 03:04:10.560
from all buyers is equal to

03:04:10.570 --> 03:04:12.520
the supply on this market

03:04:12.530 --> 03:04:13.940
from all sellers.

03:04:14.780 --> 03:04:17.000
Now look at the right schedule.

03:04:17.280 --> 03:04:21.240
You see, on the X axis I postpone and

03:04:21.250 --> 03:04:23.200
indicate the output, production, volume

03:04:23.500 --> 03:04:25.060
of the cumal.

03:04:26.260 --> 03:04:29.340
It is a separate company.

03:04:29.620 --> 03:04:31.700
This is, in a way, my tomato

03:04:31.710 --> 03:04:33.120
acquaintance.

03:04:33.900 --> 03:04:36.780
If on the left chart the bill goes for

03:04:36.790 --> 03:04:39.360
thousands of tons, then on the right

03:04:39.370 --> 03:04:41.200
chart it only goes for tons.

03:04:41.900 --> 03:04:44.560
It is a sandstone on a market scale.

03:04:44.570 --> 03:04:48.240
And it takes the existing

03:04:48.250 --> 03:04:52.800
market price P with a star as a set.

03:04:53.460 --> 03:04:55.700
As economists say, it is

03:04:55.710 --> 03:05:00.680
a price-taker, the price recipient.

03:05:02.130 --> 03:05:03.950
She takes this price as

03:05:03.960 --> 03:05:06.470
a set and can sell any quantity

03:05:06.480 --> 03:05:10.150
of her tomatoes at that price.

03:05:12.230 --> 03:05:14.570
Note that in perfect competition,

03:05:14.580 --> 03:05:17.690
it cannot raise the

03:05:17.700 --> 03:05:19.050
price.

03:05:19.870 --> 03:05:22.330
No one will buy tomatoes.

03:05:22.570 --> 03:05:25.770
What’s the point of having hundreds

03:05:25.780 --> 03:05:27.850
of sellers with a lower price?

03:05:28.590 --> 03:05:31.630
And it makes no sense to lower

03:05:31.950 --> 03:05:34.690
the price, because at this price

03:05:34.700 --> 03:05:36.790
she can sell any amount of

03:05:36.800 --> 03:05:37.570
her tomatoes.

03:05:38.900 --> 03:05:41.720
It was you and I who saw the first

03:05:41.730 --> 03:05:44.020
sign of perfect competition.

03:05:44.700 --> 03:05:48.040
Let us go back to our signs,

03:05:48.050 --> 03:05:51.520
let us look at the second sign.

03:05:52.060 --> 03:05:54.380
Full homogeneity of products,

03:05:54.540 --> 03:05:56.180
lack of trademarks.

03:05:57.140 --> 03:05:58.200
What does this mean?

03:05:59.770 --> 03:06:05.090
The products of different sellers

03:06:05.100 --> 03:06:07.230
are completely the same in

03:06:07.240 --> 03:06:08.670
the representation of buyers.

03:06:09.330 --> 03:06:12.450
Buyers do not distinguish the product

03:06:12.460 --> 03:06:14.930
of one seller from another and

03:06:14.940 --> 03:06:17.310
the seller himself from the other.

03:06:17.730 --> 03:06:19.290
But when you come to the real

03:06:19.300 --> 03:06:21.370
tomato market, agree, you will

03:06:21.380 --> 03:06:22.750
still walk in the rows, you

03:06:23.150 --> 03:06:24.150
will watch.

03:06:24.610 --> 03:06:26.530
Here, it seems tomatoes are

03:06:26.540 --> 03:06:29.470
red, but this seller seems

03:06:29.480 --> 03:06:31.930
to break a little confidence.

03:06:32.170 --> 03:06:34.250
This is not possible

03:06:34.260 --> 03:06:35.950
in perfect competition.

03:06:36.210 --> 03:06:40.010
All sellers on one person and all

03:06:40.020 --> 03:06:42.610
products are absolutely the same,

03:06:42.750 --> 03:06:43.770
no differences.

03:06:45.230 --> 03:06:48.170
Look at the third sign.

03:06:48.670 --> 03:06:51.090
Free entry and access

03:06:51.100 --> 03:06:53.350
to the market.

03:06:54.860 --> 03:06:58.180
This means that there are no barriers,

03:06:58.190 --> 03:07:00.820
financial, administrative,

03:07:00.960 --> 03:07:03.040
any, that prevented it from

03:07:03.050 --> 03:07:05.420
entering the market of new sellers

03:07:05.430 --> 03:07:08.880
or the departure of sellers

03:07:08.890 --> 03:07:10.800
from this market.

03:07:12.960 --> 03:07:16.560
Let us try this example for the

03:07:16.570 --> 03:07:19.600
discharge.

03:07:19.980 --> 03:07:23.480
Somewhere I read that our current

03:07:23.490 --> 03:07:26.640
president Vladimir Putin in his

03:07:29.010 --> 03:07:30.960
temporary, worked private transportation

03:07:30.970 --> 03:07:33.560
on his jigul.

03:07:33.820 --> 03:07:35.100
What did it mean?

03:07:35.580 --> 03:07:37.260
That he just one day sat down

03:07:37.270 --> 03:07:39.720
at the wheel of his car, went

03:07:40.120 --> 03:07:41.540
to the streets of St. Petersburg,

03:07:41.550 --> 03:07:44.620
that is, entered the private

03:07:44.630 --> 03:07:46.020
market.

03:07:47.720 --> 03:07:50.260
A while later, Vladimir Vladimirovich

03:07:50.270 --> 03:07:52.440
found an interesting job

03:07:52.450 --> 03:07:54.880
as President of Russia.

03:07:55.060 --> 03:07:57.920
This means only that he quietly

03:07:57.930 --> 03:07:59.620
put his jigguls in the garage

03:07:59.630 --> 03:08:02.000
and went to work in the Kremlin.

03:08:02.220 --> 03:08:04.440
As easily he entered the market,

03:08:04.450 --> 03:08:07.480
so easily he left it.

03:08:07.760 --> 03:08:09.900
This is a sign of perfect competition.

03:08:10.160 --> 03:08:12.280
There are no barriers to entry

03:08:12.290 --> 03:08:12.920
and exit.

03:08:15.500 --> 03:08:17.000
The fourth sign.

03:08:17.360 --> 03:08:20.320
Perfect knowledge of the market

03:08:20.330 --> 03:08:23.980
by sellers and buyers.

03:08:24.160 --> 03:08:27.200
Again, if you come to the real

03:08:27.210 --> 03:08:31.920
tomato market, then you’ll

03:08:31.930 --> 03:08:34.600
probably walk in the rows,

03:08:34.920 --> 03:08:36.200
again, looking.

03:08:36.440 --> 03:08:38.580
Maybe there are tomatoes

03:08:38.590 --> 03:08:41.260
better or a little cheaper.

03:08:42.790 --> 03:08:44.050
This is not possible in

03:08:44.060 --> 03:08:45.170
perfect competition.

03:08:45.950 --> 03:08:50.670
All sellers and all buyers are there.

03:08:50.950 --> 03:08:53.870
They seem to be together at one point.

03:08:53.950 --> 03:08:56.030
All market information

03:08:56.040 --> 03:08:58.750
is instantly disclosed.

03:08:59.050 --> 03:09:01.530
It is equally available to

03:09:01.540 --> 03:09:03.290
all sellers and all buyers.

03:09:04.840 --> 03:09:09.260
Well, if you summarize all that

03:09:09.270 --> 03:09:11.860
I said, you will probably

03:09:12.000 --> 03:09:14.580
agree that perfect competition

03:09:14.590 --> 03:09:17.480
is abstraction.

03:09:18.640 --> 03:09:23.100
Such a market does not really exist.

03:09:23.260 --> 03:09:26.900
There are markets that are more or

03:09:26.910 --> 03:09:30.500
less close to this ideal, but there

03:09:30.510 --> 03:09:31.580
is no perfectly competitive

03:09:31.590 --> 03:09:32.980
market in reality.

03:09:34.750 --> 03:09:35.330
Then the question.

03:09:36.470 --> 03:09:38.310
If there are no competitive

03:09:38.320 --> 03:09:41.170
markets, why study them?

03:09:41.850 --> 03:09:43.910
The answer is very simple.

03:09:44.130 --> 03:09:47.310
For the same reason that the chemist

03:09:47.320 --> 03:09:49.170
studies the properties of, for

03:09:49.710 --> 03:09:51.510
example, absolutely pure distilled

03:09:51.520 --> 03:09:54.170
water, which nature does not exist either.

03:09:55.310 --> 03:09:58.850
It is simply impossible to understand

03:09:58.860 --> 03:10:01.670
the properties of any impurities unless

03:10:01.680 --> 03:10:05.250
we understand, not study the subject in

03:10:05.260 --> 03:10:06.230
some perfect state.

03:10:06.240 --> 03:10:09.430
I was talking about the first type of

03:10:09.530 --> 03:10:11.530
market, perfect competition.

03:10:12.270 --> 03:10:15.650
The second type of market is called monopoly.

03:10:17.670 --> 03:10:19.050
Read the definition.

03:10:19.870 --> 03:10:21.510
Monopoly is a market structure

03:10:21.520 --> 03:10:25.110
in which there is only one company

03:10:25.120 --> 03:10:28.690
in the market that produces

03:10:28.910 --> 03:10:32.970
a product that has no close

03:10:32.980 --> 03:10:34.030
substitute.

03:10:37.320 --> 03:10:40.030
Monopolies are found at

03:10:40.040 --> 03:10:43.570
the national, regional, most often

03:10:43.580 --> 03:10:46.810
at the local level.

03:10:47.130 --> 03:10:48.990
In Russia there are national

03:10:49.000 --> 03:10:51.210
monopolies.

03:10:51.510 --> 03:10:55.370
In particular, after the reform

03:10:55.380 --> 03:10:58.690
of RAUIS, the federal network

03:10:58.700 --> 03:11:01.590
company will monopolize

03:11:01.600 --> 03:11:04.210
the power transmission lines.

03:11:05.790 --> 03:11:08.830
Or, say, in our country,

03:11:10.340 --> 03:11:12.350
it is a national monopoly,

03:11:12.690 --> 03:11:16.650
or, say, in our city there is

03:11:16.660 --> 03:11:20.870
only one company offering certain

03:11:20.880 --> 03:11:21.750
services.

03:11:22.290 --> 03:11:24.670
It is a monopoly on the local.

03:11:26.590 --> 03:11:29.430
But the next market structure

03:11:29.440 --> 03:11:32.950
is more common - oligopoly.

03:11:35.140 --> 03:11:36.120
What is it?

03:11:36.420 --> 03:11:37.680
See the definition.

03:11:38.080 --> 03:11:41.320
Oligopoly is a market structure

03:11:41.330 --> 03:11:44.720
characterized by a small

03:11:44.730 --> 03:11:48.400
number of operating firms.

03:11:52.310 --> 03:11:53.970
Examples of oligopoly.

03:11:56.450 --> 03:11:58.450
Two airlines on one

03:11:58.460 --> 03:11:59.370
route.

03:12:00.210 --> 03:12:03.370
In Moscow, the mobile market is controlled,

03:12:03.380 --> 03:12:06.570
if I am not mistaken, by four

03:12:07.310 --> 03:12:08.430
companies.

03:12:08.510 --> 03:12:11.710
Oligopoly is defined as a situation where there

03:12:11.720 --> 03:12:16.010
are less than 20 companies in the market.

03:12:16.250 --> 03:12:17.050
This is considered

03:12:17.060 --> 03:12:19.150
an oligopolistic structure.

03:12:19.490 --> 03:12:21.570
This is a very common case

03:12:21.580 --> 03:12:23.910
of oligopoly.

03:12:25.230 --> 03:12:27.890
Oligopoly is a very interesting

03:12:27.900 --> 03:12:28.870
market structure.

03:12:32.070 --> 03:12:33.770
When we looked at

03:12:33.780 --> 03:12:35.930
perfect competition,

03:12:35.940 --> 03:12:39.950
we saw that when a single

03:12:39.960 --> 03:12:43.270
seller makes a decision,

03:12:43.280 --> 03:12:45.610
he does not look at

03:12:45.620 --> 03:12:48.250
other sellers.

03:12:48.630 --> 03:12:50.410
He is a sandstone on the scale of the

03:12:50.420 --> 03:12:52.090
market, he simply accepts the

03:12:52.100 --> 03:12:54.190
market price.

03:12:54.270 --> 03:12:56.810
The monopoly does not look at competitors,

03:12:56.820 --> 03:12:58.950
either, for the simple reason

03:12:58.960 --> 03:13:00.950
that they simply do not exist in

03:13:00.960 --> 03:13:01.690
the monopoly.

03:13:01.890 --> 03:13:07.170
But the olegopolist acts as his

03:13:07.830 --> 03:13:11.830
own capabilities and the behavior

03:13:11.840 --> 03:13:15.350
of other firms allow him.

03:13:17.260 --> 03:13:19.660
The olegopolistic situation

03:13:19.670 --> 03:13:21.940
is similar to a kind of card game

03:13:21.950 --> 03:13:27.160
where there is no single pre-

03:13:27.170 --> 03:13:29.000
set model of behavior.

03:13:29.440 --> 03:13:32.360
Each player plays as the

03:13:32.370 --> 03:13:36.400
cards are allowed and as the

03:13:36.410 --> 03:13:38.160
competitors play.

03:13:38.800 --> 03:13:40.780
In the context of oligopoly,

03:13:40.790 --> 03:13:44.380
strategic behavior is formed.

03:13:47.050 --> 03:13:52.350
At the same time, individual olegopolists

03:13:52.360 --> 03:13:54.650
can choose one or another form of

03:13:54.660 --> 03:13:57.090
rivalry, one or another strategy

03:13:57.100 --> 03:14:00.390
of rivalry or adopt a strategy

03:14:00.400 --> 03:14:03.430
of conspiracy.

03:14:03.450 --> 03:14:04.550
So happens too.

03:14:07.460 --> 03:14:09.940
The fourth type of market

03:14:09.950 --> 03:14:12.080
is monopolistic competition.

03:14:12.860 --> 03:14:14.200
Read the definition.

03:14:14.940 --> 03:14:17.400
Monopolistic competition is a

03:14:17.410 --> 03:14:20.120
market structure in which

03:14:20.130 --> 03:14:23.220
a group of goods that are close

03:14:23.230 --> 03:14:25.180
substituents are produced

03:14:25.220 --> 03:14:27.800
by a large number of independent

03:14:27.810 --> 03:14:30.280
firms.

03:14:30.680 --> 03:14:31.620
Try to explain.

03:14:33.880 --> 03:14:35.980
Let us remember the perfect

03:14:35.990 --> 03:14:38.180
competition.

03:14:39.440 --> 03:14:42.240
There were a lot of firms there.

03:14:43.560 --> 03:14:46.000
In theory, it is infinite.

03:14:47.060 --> 03:14:50.100
In the conditions of monopolistic

03:14:50.110 --> 03:14:52.600
competition, may not be so

03:14:52.610 --> 03:14:54.060
many, but also very many.

03:14:54.560 --> 03:14:57.740
But there are fundamental differences.

03:14:58.180 --> 03:15:00.300
Remember, I said that in perfect

03:15:00.310 --> 03:15:04.640
competition, the products of individual

03:15:04.650 --> 03:15:07.400
firms are absolutely indistinguishable

03:15:07.410 --> 03:15:10.340
in the eyes of the buyers.

03:15:10.600 --> 03:15:12.640
The companies are completely the same.

03:15:12.960 --> 03:15:14.920
This is not the case

03:15:14.930 --> 03:15:16.520
with monopolistic competition.

03:15:16.780 --> 03:15:21.460
Here, each company has a certain distinction

03:15:21.470 --> 03:15:26.340
that distinguishes it, its products

03:15:26.350 --> 03:15:30.760
or its own from other firms.

03:15:34.300 --> 03:15:40.760
It is a mini monopoly.

03:15:41.320 --> 03:15:44.000
It is a mini-monopoly in a very narrow

03:15:44.010 --> 03:15:46.580
segment of the market.

03:15:46.590 --> 03:15:47.360
Here is example.

03:15:48.080 --> 03:15:51.520
There are many cafes in our city, but

03:15:51.530 --> 03:15:55.800
I distinguish this cafe from what.

03:15:56.280 --> 03:15:58.440
Maybe it’s a cafe, I think, maybe

03:15:58.450 --> 03:16:00.860
it’s a better place to eat in this

03:16:00.870 --> 03:16:02.680
cafe, maybe there’s a more

03:16:02.690 --> 03:16:05.100
sympathetic waitress, maybe the

03:16:05.110 --> 03:16:07.520
interior is more attractive, or

03:16:07.530 --> 03:16:08.740
maybe this cafe is just

03:16:08.750 --> 03:16:10.620
located closer to my home.

03:16:12.170 --> 03:16:15.820
That is, in the conditions

03:16:15.830 --> 03:16:18.260
of monopolistic competition, I repeat

03:16:18.270 --> 03:16:22.520
again, individual firms, possessing

03:16:22.920 --> 03:16:25.200
some distinctive features,

03:16:25.210 --> 03:16:27.760
possess a small but still

03:16:27.770 --> 03:16:29.780
monopolistic power in

03:16:29.790 --> 03:16:32.220
a narrow segment of the

03:16:32.230 --> 03:16:33.400
market.

03:16:34.850 --> 03:16:38.320
And now look, it is necessary

03:16:38.330 --> 03:16:42.080
to distinguish between pure

03:16:42.090 --> 03:16:47.860
monopoly and monopoly power.

03:16:48.680 --> 03:16:51.520
Monopoly power arises where

03:16:52.260 --> 03:16:56.180
a single firm has some

03:16:56.190 --> 03:16:58.580
control over the price.

03:17:03.370 --> 03:17:07.130
It can change the price within

03:17:07.140 --> 03:17:10.670
certain limits.

03:17:12.230 --> 03:17:14.590
This is not the case with perfect competition.

03:17:15.010 --> 03:17:18.510
Please look at the left schedule.

03:17:18.990 --> 03:17:20.630
On the left is a very competitive

03:17:20.640 --> 03:17:22.590
company.

03:17:22.970 --> 03:17:25.370
I have already said that in perfect

03:17:25.380 --> 03:17:28.190
competition, a single firm,

03:17:28.200 --> 03:17:31.450
being a sandstone on the general

03:17:31.460 --> 03:17:33.750
market scale, can sell

03:17:33.760 --> 03:17:35.910
any quantity of its products

03:17:35.920 --> 03:17:39.050
at the market price.

03:17:39.350 --> 03:17:42.390
The function of demand for a product

03:17:42.400 --> 03:17:45.010
of a completely competitive company

03:17:45.020 --> 03:17:47.290
is a horizontal line.

03:17:47.670 --> 03:17:51.770
The market can buy any quantity

03:17:51.780 --> 03:17:54.810
of its products at the current

03:17:54.820 --> 03:17:56.750
market price.

03:17:57.530 --> 03:17:59.410
Changing the price of a completely

03:17:59.420 --> 03:18:01.930
competitive company cannot by definition.

03:18:02.750 --> 03:18:04.290
But a firm with a monopoly

03:18:04.300 --> 03:18:06.730
power may change the price to

03:18:06.740 --> 03:18:08.790
a greater or lesser extent.

03:18:08.970 --> 03:18:11.370
Please look at the right schedule.

03:18:11.510 --> 03:18:13.430
There, the demand function for the

03:18:13.440 --> 03:18:16.090
company's product has a negative slope.

03:18:18.840 --> 03:18:22.140
This means that the company can

03:18:22.150 --> 03:18:24.600
raise or lower the price.

03:18:24.610 --> 03:18:29.180
But it is clear that by raising the

03:18:29.280 --> 03:18:31.220
price, it will face a decrease in

03:18:31.230 --> 03:18:33.060
demand for its product.

03:18:34.220 --> 03:18:38.780
And if the price is lower, it will face its increase.

03:18:39.280 --> 03:18:42.040
No super monopoly can abolish

03:18:42.050 --> 03:18:45.180
the laws of demand.

03:18:45.190 --> 03:18:49.460
But what is obvious is that it is important

03:18:49.470 --> 03:18:54.100
that the more the slope of demand

03:18:54.110 --> 03:18:58.360
for a company's product, the lower

03:18:58.370 --> 03:19:00.500
its monopoly power.

03:19:01.900 --> 03:19:07.400
So I have just said that by the inclination

03:19:07.410 --> 03:19:11.200
of the demand function on a firm’

03:19:11.210 --> 03:19:14.740
s product, one can judge how

03:19:14.750 --> 03:19:17.020
great its monopoly power is.

03:19:27.850 --> 03:19:28.790
Well, please look at the quantity of the

03:19:29.170 --> 03:19:30.390
goods, as always, the price of the goods,

03:19:33.140 --> 03:19:37.260
and let’s say the function of demand

03:19:37.270 --> 03:19:39.420
is going like this.

03:19:43.400 --> 03:19:45.270
Look what it means.

03:19:45.310 --> 03:19:47.610
You see, the function has a

03:19:47.620 --> 03:19:48.830
fairly high tilt.

03:19:54.060 --> 03:19:58.940
So, a firm can raise the price quite

03:19:58.950 --> 03:20:02.440
significantly from P0 to P1, see,

03:20:02.620 --> 03:20:04.680
a significant price increase, without

03:20:04.690 --> 03:20:09.060
fear of losing a large volume

03:20:09.070 --> 03:20:10.040
of demand.

03:20:20.580 --> 03:20:24.660
In other words, it is difficult for the consumer

03:20:24.670 --> 03:20:27.080
to do without the product of this company.

03:20:27.720 --> 03:20:30.800
Even with a large price rise, the

03:20:30.810 --> 03:20:34.240
fall in demand will be minor.

03:20:35.420 --> 03:20:38.420
We say that the company

03:20:38.430 --> 03:20:41.140
has a high monopoly power.

03:20:43.070 --> 03:20:45.290
Now imagine a monopoly

03:20:45.300 --> 03:20:47.530
competitive company.

03:20:48.230 --> 03:20:51.370
The function of demand for its product goes

03:20:51.380 --> 03:20:53.190
very much by logo.

03:20:58.530 --> 03:21:02.330
So, the company can raise the price.

03:21:02.350 --> 03:21:05.350
This is the demand function for its product.

03:21:05.690 --> 03:21:07.630
But note, the company has

03:21:07.950 --> 03:21:11.670
raised the price very slightly.

03:21:12.810 --> 03:21:14.830
How much did you lose in demand?

03:21:17.790 --> 03:21:18.950
very much.

03:21:19.210 --> 03:21:22.790
A slight price increase has led

03:21:22.800 --> 03:21:25.390
to a significant decline in demand.

03:21:25.400 --> 03:21:26.250
Why so?

03:21:27.070 --> 03:21:29.130
In the context of monopolistic

03:21:29.140 --> 03:21:31.790
competition, the product

03:21:31.800 --> 03:21:34.110
has many substitutes.

03:21:34.750 --> 03:21:37.110
Therefore, with a slight increase

03:21:37.120 --> 03:21:40.870
in the price, buyers can easily switch

03:21:40.880 --> 03:21:45.990
to the product of other companies.

03:21:47.720 --> 03:21:49.160
What extreme case?

03:21:49.340 --> 03:21:53.140
The perfect competition.

03:21:53.420 --> 03:21:56.640
When the line of demand for the

03:21:56.650 --> 03:22:00.840
company’s product becomes such a slope

03:22:02.180 --> 03:22:06.260
that it becomes horizontal.

03:22:07.200 --> 03:22:09.220
The company has no

03:22:09.230 --> 03:22:11.180
control over the market

03:22:11.190 --> 03:22:12.540
price.

03:22:12.760 --> 03:22:17.360
He can only accept the price.

03:22:17.370 --> 03:22:23.180
Now let us look at the reasons

03:22:23.500 --> 03:22:25.840
why monopoly power

03:22:25.850 --> 03:22:29.800
can arise and exist.

03:22:30.160 --> 03:22:34.060
I identify three reasons.

03:22:34.200 --> 03:22:36.380
The first reason is very simple.

03:22:36.440 --> 03:22:38.620
Exclusive rights

03:22:38.630 --> 03:22:41.020
granted by authorities.

03:22:42.880 --> 03:22:45.620
Well, let’s say, local

03:22:45.630 --> 03:22:48.860
or regional authorities,

03:22:48.870 --> 03:22:52.120
or all-Russian authorities, only my

03:22:52.130 --> 03:22:55.260
firm is allowed to engage in this

03:22:55.270 --> 03:22:56.240
type of activity.

03:22:56.920 --> 03:22:59.200
Other companies simply do not

03:22:59.210 --> 03:23:01.100
get the appropriate license.

03:23:02.420 --> 03:23:06.200
This leads to an administrative

03:23:06.210 --> 03:23:08.360
monopoly.

03:23:08.480 --> 03:23:13.480
If the license is granted to several

03:23:13.490 --> 03:23:18.700
companies, we are given an administrative oligopoly.

03:23:19.140 --> 03:23:21.940
Now let us talk about the second reason

03:23:21.950 --> 03:23:25.660
for the existence of monopoly power.

03:23:26.560 --> 03:23:29.260
It is the exclusive ownership

03:23:29.270 --> 03:23:31.760
of any production resource.

03:23:32.160 --> 03:23:34.780
I have said many times that

03:23:34.790 --> 03:23:37.120
to do something, you need

03:23:37.380 --> 03:23:38.500
resources.

03:23:39.180 --> 03:23:41.120
Imagine, please, that some important

03:23:41.130 --> 03:23:43.760
resource for the production

03:23:43.770 --> 03:23:48.000
of this product is in the

03:23:48.010 --> 03:23:50.040
exclusive property

03:23:50.050 --> 03:23:53.060
of this firm.

03:23:53.580 --> 03:23:55.600
Only she can produce

03:23:55.610 --> 03:23:57.160
this product.

03:23:57.170 --> 03:23:59.420
Others can’t, and our company

03:23:59.430 --> 03:24:02.540
is a monopolist.

03:24:03.260 --> 03:24:04.040
The example.

03:24:06.460 --> 03:24:09.060
Alcoa was once the monopoly

03:24:09.070 --> 03:24:12.440
on the American aluminum

03:24:12.450 --> 03:24:14.320
market.

03:24:14.640 --> 03:24:16.900
Her monopoly was based on

03:24:16.910 --> 03:24:19.200
the fact that she alone

03:24:19.210 --> 03:24:21.660
owned all the bacit fields

03:24:21.670 --> 03:24:23.040
in Chile.

03:24:24.980 --> 03:24:29.200
Only a surgeon can perform

03:24:29.210 --> 03:24:31.300
this operation.

03:24:32.120 --> 03:24:37.880
He is the monopolist of his talent.

03:24:38.180 --> 03:24:40.100
Only he has the teaching talent,

03:24:40.110 --> 03:24:43.040
and on this basis there

03:24:43.050 --> 03:24:45.320
is a monopoly.

03:24:49.540 --> 03:24:53.980
Or only this company has a patent

03:24:53.990 --> 03:24:55.920
on the latest technological

03:24:55.930 --> 03:24:57.620
development.

03:24:58.100 --> 03:25:01.600
It is becoming a monopoly.

03:25:01.920 --> 03:25:04.640
If a resource belongs to

03:25:04.650 --> 03:25:07.080
several firms, it is no longer

03:25:09.280 --> 03:25:13.180
a monopoly, but an oligopoly.

03:25:17.140 --> 03:25:20.240
The third reason for monopoly power

03:25:20.250 --> 03:25:24.780
is the increasing return on scale.

03:25:25.960 --> 03:25:27.120
Here it is a little more difficult.

03:25:28.320 --> 03:25:32.180
Let us remember what is

03:25:32.190 --> 03:25:35.920
increasing return on scale.

03:25:36.140 --> 03:25:37.780
What does she mean?

03:25:38.380 --> 03:25:39.580
When does it emerge?

03:25:39.620 --> 03:25:41.740
When do we talk about increasing

03:25:41.750 --> 03:25:43.280
scale?

03:25:47.580 --> 03:25:50.260
When the number of resources

03:25:50.270 --> 03:25:53.440
used increases by N times, production

03:25:53.450 --> 03:25:57.140
increases by more than

03:25:57.150 --> 03:25:58.840
N times.

03:25:59.820 --> 03:26:01.020
We talked about this, if you remember,

03:26:01.030 --> 03:26:02.860
in the previous topic.

03:26:04.680 --> 03:26:07.520
But if there is an increasing return

03:26:07.530 --> 03:26:10.200
on scale, it means that

03:26:10.210 --> 03:26:16.820
the larger the output, the less

03:26:19.170 --> 03:26:22.330
the company costs per unit

03:26:22.340 --> 03:26:23.470
of products.

03:26:24.310 --> 03:26:25.970
Think really.

03:26:27.880 --> 03:26:35.000
The company is twice as large

03:26:35.540 --> 03:26:37.780
as a small company.

03:26:37.790 --> 03:26:41.500
It uses twice as much labor

03:26:41.510 --> 03:26:43.180
and capital.

03:26:44.400 --> 03:26:48.580
And the output of it increases by three times

03:26:48.590 --> 03:26:49.520
at the same time.

03:26:50.420 --> 03:26:53.740
This means that the unit

03:26:53.750 --> 03:26:57.000
cost of the product will be less.

03:26:58.380 --> 03:27:03.560
So, in this case, the larger the volume

03:27:03.570 --> 03:27:08.900
of production, the less the cost per

03:27:08.910 --> 03:27:11.500
unit of products.

03:27:13.960 --> 03:27:19.360
Once that happens, the companies are starting to grow.

03:27:20.340 --> 03:27:21.880
In fact, look at it.

03:27:21.890 --> 03:27:26.980
Here is the beginning of the twentieth century.

03:27:28.080 --> 03:27:30.040
Dozens of independent companies

03:27:30.050 --> 03:27:32.960
operated in the United

03:27:32.970 --> 03:27:34.040
States.

03:27:35.400 --> 03:27:36.620
What happens next?

03:27:39.020 --> 03:27:43.000
With the cash, several firms have grown.

03:27:44.580 --> 03:27:47.500
The amount of resources increased in

03:27:47.510 --> 03:27:49.980
them, well, suppose, conditionally twice.

03:27:51.780 --> 03:27:55.440
The output has increased four

03:27:55.450 --> 03:27:56.160
times.

03:27:56.940 --> 03:27:59.940
So, the larger company

03:27:59.950 --> 03:28:03.200
costs per unit of product.

03:28:03.720 --> 03:28:06.120
Less than smaller companies.

03:28:06.380 --> 03:28:07.560
What does this lead to?

03:28:08.240 --> 03:28:10.600
Big companies are growing,

03:28:10.610 --> 03:28:13.580
small companies are breaking down.

03:28:13.980 --> 03:28:16.660
In the end, there may be

03:28:16.670 --> 03:28:19.260
only one company on

03:28:19.270 --> 03:28:20.440
the market.

03:28:21.400 --> 03:28:24.060
If there are several companies in the market,

03:28:24.070 --> 03:28:30.520
we are talking about a natural oligopoly.

03:28:30.880 --> 03:28:33.020
See the definition

03:28:33.320 --> 03:28:37.980
of natural monopoly.

03:28:38.740 --> 03:28:40.940
The natural monopoly.

03:28:41.560 --> 03:28:44.740
A natural monopoly is a company

03:28:44.750 --> 03:28:48.760
that can meet any market demand

03:28:48.770 --> 03:28:51.780
with small and lower long-

03:28:51.790 --> 03:28:53.660
term average costs than those

03:28:53.670 --> 03:28:56.060
that would have been

03:28:56.070 --> 03:28:59.200
created if two or more

03:28:59.210 --> 03:29:02.180
companies were in the

03:29:02.190 --> 03:29:03.940
market instead.

03:29:06.120 --> 03:29:09.140
What is the nature of

03:29:09.150 --> 03:29:10.380
natural monopoly?

03:29:12.160 --> 03:29:15.930
The fact that its special monopoly

03:29:15.940 --> 03:29:20.210
position is not based on

03:29:20.220 --> 03:29:23.490
administrative resources, not

03:29:23.500 --> 03:29:25.310
on some other factors that can be

03:29:27.340 --> 03:29:30.210
eliminated in principle, and

03:29:30.220 --> 03:29:33.910
its monopoly position is based

03:29:33.920 --> 03:29:36.850
on the cost advantages.

03:29:36.860 --> 03:29:38.470
Hence an important conclusion.

03:29:39.330 --> 03:29:41.510
It is pointless to fight

03:29:41.520 --> 03:29:45.070
against natural monopoly by its scaling.

03:29:47.330 --> 03:29:51.670
If we create two instead of one

03:29:51.680 --> 03:29:53.510
large firm, which is a natural

03:29:55.590 --> 03:29:58.580
monopoly, the production of

03:29:58.590 --> 03:30:01.820
each will be twice as small as that

03:30:02.140 --> 03:30:03.280
of a large firm.

03:30:05.560 --> 03:30:08.960
The cost will be higher

03:30:08.970 --> 03:30:10.960
per unit of product.

03:30:12.690 --> 03:30:14.690
Well, here I will try

03:30:14.700 --> 03:30:17.290
to illustrate the natural monopoly

03:30:17.300 --> 03:30:19.570
by a number of examples.

03:30:21.000 --> 03:30:22.400
Here is the simplest example.

03:30:24.470 --> 03:30:31.910
In our homes in the kitchen two pipes,

03:30:32.450 --> 03:30:35.150
one with hot water, the other with cold water.

03:30:37.830 --> 03:30:41.470
Water to our homes is supplied by one company,

03:30:41.480 --> 03:30:44.350
the water channel bridge.

03:30:45.510 --> 03:30:47.610
But monopoly is bad, most

03:30:48.750 --> 03:30:49.910
often.

03:30:50.790 --> 03:30:52.950
And, well, when monopoly is usually

03:30:52.960 --> 03:30:56.070
overpriced, it is usually

03:30:57.430 --> 03:30:58.190
low quality.

03:30:58.750 --> 03:31:00.190
Why then, if the monopoly is bad,

03:31:00.200 --> 03:31:03.630
why do we then, in pursuit of competition,

03:31:03.640 --> 03:31:07.470
do not carry on every kitchen

03:31:07.480 --> 03:31:10.330
a lot of hot and cold water

03:31:10.340 --> 03:31:11.450
pipes, belonging to

03:31:11.490 --> 03:31:13.630
different companies?

03:31:13.750 --> 03:31:14.850
Companies could compete

03:31:14.860 --> 03:31:16.310
with each other.

03:31:16.830 --> 03:31:20.110
And we could choose the water

03:31:20.270 --> 03:31:23.330
that is cheaper or, say, cleaner.

03:31:23.870 --> 03:31:27.790
It is not done for a very simple reason.

03:31:28.150 --> 03:31:32.310
The cost of each liter of water will increase.

03:31:32.550 --> 03:31:34.290
Here is a very conditional example.

03:31:37.990 --> 03:31:42.630
Suppose the consumption of water

03:31:42.640 --> 03:31:44.450
per unit of time, no matter, a year,

03:31:44.630 --> 03:31:46.650
a month, a day, is conditionally

03:31:46.660 --> 03:31:48.470
100 liters.

03:31:53.610 --> 03:31:55.710
To bring a pipeline with water into the

03:31:55.720 --> 03:31:58.630
apartment, you need to spend 100 rubles.

03:32:04.300 --> 03:32:07.340
The cost of one liter of

03:32:07.350 --> 03:32:12.100
water is one ruble.

03:32:16.140 --> 03:32:18.460
Now imagine that in pursuit of competition

03:32:18.470 --> 03:32:22.500
we have spent at least two pipes

03:32:22.510 --> 03:32:25.940
in the apartment, supplying water,

03:32:26.240 --> 03:32:28.320
which is delivered by

03:32:28.330 --> 03:32:30.740
different companies.

03:32:31.000 --> 03:32:33.540
Two different companies supply water to

03:32:33.550 --> 03:32:33.960
our homes.

03:32:34.240 --> 03:32:38.380
But then, if two pipes, the cost of

03:32:38.390 --> 03:32:42.420
the padding will increase exactly twice

03:32:42.430 --> 03:32:46.120
and now make up 200 rubles in total.

03:32:52.250 --> 03:32:54.970
And the consumption of water in the

03:32:54.980 --> 03:32:56.770
apartment will remain, it will not change

03:32:56.780 --> 03:32:59.110
from this, will remain as -still 100 liters.

03:32:59.770 --> 03:33:00.950
And what will happen?

03:33:07.700 --> 03:33:14.700
The cost of each liter is 2 rubles.

03:33:14.710 --> 03:33:18.780
So, this means that it is not profitable

03:33:18.790 --> 03:33:23.020
to create several companies competing

03:33:23.030 --> 03:33:24.860
with each other instead

03:33:24.870 --> 03:33:26.240
of one monopoly.

03:33:27.040 --> 03:33:31.620
The unit cost of products will increase.

03:33:31.920 --> 03:33:34.220
This is a natural monopoly.

03:33:34.640 --> 03:33:37.260
I repeat, a natural monopoly is

03:33:37.270 --> 03:33:41.760
a firm whose monopoly position

03:33:41.770 --> 03:33:42.760
is based on cost

03:33:44.760 --> 03:33:47.230
advantages and is associated

03:33:47.240 --> 03:33:50.210
with increasing scale returns.

03:33:50.230 --> 03:33:52.030
If we create several companies

03:33:52.040 --> 03:33:55.110
instead of one, the cost

03:33:55.120 --> 03:33:57.810
per unit of the product

03:33:57.820 --> 03:33:59.950
will increase.

03:34:00.250 --> 03:34:01.350
How did we get it?

03:34:01.390 --> 03:34:04.250
In my conditional example.

03:34:04.510 --> 03:34:05.230
Another example.

03:34:06.110 --> 03:34:07.410
RAU of Russia.

03:34:09.250 --> 03:34:11.490
This company is doing a lot

03:34:11.500 --> 03:34:12.270
now.

03:34:12.310 --> 03:34:14.070
It is engaged in both

03:34:16.150 --> 03:34:18.280
power generation and

03:34:18.290 --> 03:34:20.220
transmission through

03:34:20.230 --> 03:34:22.880
power lines and through

03:34:22.890 --> 03:34:25.440
its subsidiaries.

03:34:30.990 --> 03:34:35.210
Well, look, let’s say, it’s all power

03:34:35.220 --> 03:34:38.170
plants that generate companies.

03:34:42.350 --> 03:34:44.390
This is the electric transmission line.

03:34:51.390 --> 03:34:55.580
It is the sale of electricity to consumers.

03:34:58.460 --> 03:35:00.780
Which of these three

03:35:00.790 --> 03:35:04.600
areas of activity is a

03:35:04.610 --> 03:35:06.120
natural monopoly?

03:35:12.200 --> 03:35:14.980
Clear electric transmission line.

03:35:17.070 --> 03:35:20.070
The reform of the RAO of the

03:35:20.080 --> 03:35:22.130
EU envisages its elimination in its

03:35:22.140 --> 03:35:22.730
present form.

03:35:23.850 --> 03:35:26.690
From the RAO of the EU will

03:35:26.700 --> 03:35:28.710
be separated as independent firms

03:35:28.720 --> 03:35:31.250
wholesale generating companies

03:35:31.260 --> 03:35:34.210
and territorial generating companies.

03:35:34.590 --> 03:35:39.070
Generation can be in the field of competition.

03:35:39.330 --> 03:35:41.390
Generating companies can

03:35:41.400 --> 03:35:43.430
compete with each other.

03:35:43.650 --> 03:35:45.350
There is no natural monopoly.

03:35:46.490 --> 03:35:48.950
The electricity transmission line should

03:35:48.960 --> 03:35:49.670
be one.

03:35:50.370 --> 03:35:53.350
Because if we put another line

03:35:53.360 --> 03:36:00.030
next to that line for competition.

03:36:00.230 --> 03:36:02.670
The cost of the installation will increase

03:36:02.680 --> 03:36:04.130
exactly twice.

03:36:04.450 --> 03:36:06.930
The cost of each kilowatt hour of

03:36:06.940 --> 03:36:08.810
electricity transmission

03:36:08.820 --> 03:36:11.150
will increase.

03:36:11.430 --> 03:36:13.870
The electricity transmission line

03:36:13.880 --> 03:36:15.170
is a natural monopoly.

03:36:15.630 --> 03:36:19.450
And after the reform of the RAU

03:36:19.460 --> 03:36:21.990
EU, the power transmission line will

03:36:22.000 --> 03:36:25.030
remain owned by the federal network company.

03:36:25.190 --> 03:36:27.470
This would be a natural monopoly

03:36:28.050 --> 03:36:29.410
in which the control of the stock

03:36:29.420 --> 03:36:30.630
is owned by the state.

03:36:32.430 --> 03:36:33.250
well well well.

03:36:34.290 --> 03:36:41.200
And if we take the sphere of Gazprom,

03:36:41.210 --> 03:36:45.100
what is there a natural monopoly?

03:36:48.890 --> 03:36:50.610
Gas pipelines obviously.

03:36:52.680 --> 03:36:54.320
Independent companies

03:36:54.330 --> 03:36:55.860
can produce gas.

03:36:55.960 --> 03:37:01.310
But here is the pipe, until it is of course

03:37:01.320 --> 03:37:04.330
not filled to the end, it is better

03:37:04.340 --> 03:37:05.150
if there is only one.

03:37:05.710 --> 03:37:08.710
Otherwise, the cost of gas transmission will increase.

03:37:09.010 --> 03:37:11.830
Every unit of gas, I mean, will grow.

03:37:12.210 --> 03:37:15.850
In the RAO and RZD field,

03:37:15.860 --> 03:37:17.050
the Russian railways are

03:37:17.060 --> 03:37:18.610
a natural monopoly.

03:37:19.850 --> 03:37:21.970
The roads and all

03:37:21.980 --> 03:37:23.530
the railway infrastructure.

03:37:25.240 --> 03:37:27.580
Vans and locomotives are

03:37:27.590 --> 03:37:29.380
private property.

03:37:29.390 --> 03:37:30.540
It is owned by independent

03:37:30.550 --> 03:37:32.260
competing companies.

03:37:33.120 --> 03:37:35.440
They are not natural monopolies.

03:37:36.140 --> 03:37:37.220
This is actually going on.

03:37:37.620 --> 03:37:40.420
Sooner or later, only roads and infrastructure

03:37:40.430 --> 03:37:44.420
will remain in the property of RAO and the Railway.

03:37:45.000 --> 03:37:46.000
The rest will be owned

03:37:46.010 --> 03:37:47.860
by independent firms that

03:37:48.020 --> 03:37:49.960
will compete with each other.

03:37:50.660 --> 03:37:54.480
So, we have looked at the different

03:37:54.490 --> 03:37:58.160
types of existing market structures.

03:37:59.910 --> 03:38:02.870
Now, we go to the second issue of this topic.

03:38:02.970 --> 03:38:04.430
income of the company.

03:38:06.090 --> 03:38:09.390
First of all, the concept of gross

03:38:09.400 --> 03:38:12.670
income or revenue of the company.

03:38:14.290 --> 03:38:17.370
It is marked by the letters TR Total Revenue.

03:38:17.570 --> 03:38:19.430
gross income or income.

03:38:20.110 --> 03:38:21.070
What is it?

03:38:21.710 --> 03:38:22.670
It is very simple.

03:38:23.190 --> 03:38:26.430
The revenue of the company is the product of the

03:38:26.440 --> 03:38:30.050
price of the goods on the volume of production.

03:38:30.870 --> 03:38:32.850
On the slide you can see the formula.

03:38:32.910 --> 03:38:36.470
TR is equal to P multiplied by Q.

03:38:37.210 --> 03:38:39.210
The usual formula of revenue.

03:38:40.090 --> 03:38:42.530
Another term used is the average

03:38:42.540 --> 03:38:44.490
income of the company.

03:38:45.830 --> 03:38:47.370
The average income of the company.

03:38:47.380 --> 03:38:48.670
Look at the slide.

03:38:49.050 --> 03:38:53.250
This is a private revenue division on the

03:38:53.260 --> 03:38:55.510
volume of release or implementation.

03:38:58.350 --> 03:39:02.790
But it is not difficult to understand that

03:39:02.800 --> 03:39:07.370
if the revenue on the volume of release will get the price.

03:39:07.950 --> 03:39:12.010
So average income is just another

03:39:12.020 --> 03:39:13.890
name for price.

03:39:20.210 --> 03:39:23.250
Graphically, it is possible to build

03:39:25.890 --> 03:39:28.680
a revenue function if we deal with

03:39:28.690 --> 03:39:31.320
a completely competitive company.

03:39:32.520 --> 03:39:34.440
What is different, remember?

03:39:36.580 --> 03:39:40.210
A completely competitive company

03:39:40.220 --> 03:39:42.770
has a price set.

03:39:43.410 --> 03:39:46.530
The company cannot change the price.

03:39:48.130 --> 03:39:51.050
And hence it follows that the function

03:39:51.060 --> 03:39:53.830
of revenue from the release of a completely

03:39:53.840 --> 03:39:56.810
competitive firm is a linear function

03:39:56.820 --> 03:40:00.270
that comes from the beginning of the coordinate.

03:40:00.750 --> 03:40:04.170
With zero release, the revenue is zero.

03:40:04.180 --> 03:40:09.590
In the single issue, we get the issue

03:40:09.600 --> 03:40:12.610
multiplied by the given price and

03:40:12.620 --> 03:40:13.710
so on.

03:40:14.610 --> 03:40:16.450
The function of revenue will

03:40:16.460 --> 03:40:18.230
be linear.

03:40:20.360 --> 03:40:25.140
The next very important concept in

03:40:25.150 --> 03:40:29.760
microeconomics is the limit income.

03:40:30.380 --> 03:40:32.260
Margin of Revenge.

03:40:32.840 --> 03:40:35.280
The definition of the limit income is

03:40:35.290 --> 03:40:37.440
read on the slide.

03:40:38.060 --> 03:40:40.860
The company's limit income is

03:40:40.870 --> 03:40:45.540
the increase in revenue when sales

03:40:45.550 --> 03:40:48.560
increase by one unit.

03:40:50.950 --> 03:40:55.630
That is, MR is equal to Delta

03:40:55.640 --> 03:40:57.610
TR divided by Delta Cube.

03:41:02.710 --> 03:41:04.870
Does nothing remind you of

03:41:04.880 --> 03:41:06.030
the limit income?

03:41:06.490 --> 03:41:10.950
Something of what we studied, looked

03:41:11.750 --> 03:41:14.990
at in the previous topic.

03:41:15.290 --> 03:41:16.870
Remember, in the previous topic we

03:41:16.880 --> 03:41:19.450
talked about the limit costs?

03:41:21.000 --> 03:41:22.520
Let us remember.

03:41:22.840 --> 03:41:26.620
Limit costs are the increase in total

03:41:26.630 --> 03:41:29.400
costs, with the increase in production

03:41:29.410 --> 03:41:31.920
by one unit.

03:41:32.460 --> 03:41:36.000
A marginal income is the increase in

03:41:36.010 --> 03:41:38.980
revenue, with an increase in output

03:41:38.990 --> 03:41:42.240
or sales by one unit.

03:41:42.540 --> 03:41:46.520
Accordingly, the limit income is the

03:41:46.530 --> 03:41:50.040
additional income that the company

03:41:50.440 --> 03:41:54.480
receives when it releases and sells

03:41:54.490 --> 03:41:57.860
an additional unit of the product.

