Yes, just another small comment.

03:42:10.780 --> 03:42:14.220
If we are talking about a completely competitive

03:42:14.230 --> 03:42:18.340
company, then its marginal income

03:42:18.350 --> 03:42:22.160
is equal to the price of the goods.

03:42:23.530 --> 03:42:25.690
Well, in fact, a completely

03:42:25.700 --> 03:42:29.030
competitive company sells any volume

03:42:29.040 --> 03:42:31.570
of its products at the

03:42:31.580 --> 03:42:34.890
current market price.

03:42:35.050 --> 03:42:37.070
The price for a completely competitive

03:42:37.080 --> 03:42:39.550
company is set.

03:42:42.490 --> 03:42:46.250
And if so, then each additional

03:42:46.260 --> 03:42:49.130
unit of release brings such

03:42:49.140 --> 03:42:51.870
a company an additional

03:42:51.880 --> 03:42:54.970
revenue, the additional

03:42:55.250 --> 03:42:57.770
income is equal to this

03:42:57.780 --> 03:42:59.710
price.

03:43:00.550 --> 03:43:03.610
Well, if a company, for example, sells products

03:43:03.620 --> 03:43:06.170
all the time at the price of 10 rubles,

03:43:06.180 --> 03:43:09.730
then each additional unit of release

03:43:09.740 --> 03:43:12.690
will increase the company's revenue

03:43:12.700 --> 03:43:15.350
by those same 10 rubles.

03:43:16.450 --> 03:43:17.950
The marginal income of a firm, a

03:43:17.960 --> 03:43:19.570
firm that is completely

03:43:19.580 --> 03:43:21.750
competitive, is necessarily

03:43:21.760 --> 03:43:24.370
equal to the price of the goods

03:43:24.380 --> 03:43:26.010
at which it sells its products.

