04:38:00.270 --> 04:38:02.030
On the second buyer I won 8 rubles,

04:38:02.040 --> 04:38:03.970
he brought me 8 rubles today,

04:38:03.980 --> 04:38:05.530
which yesterday did not bring me.

04:38:06.070 --> 04:38:08.830
But the first one brought me yesterday

04:38:09.110 --> 04:38:11.270
9 and today he brought only 8, I

04:38:11.280 --> 04:38:12.970
sell 8 rubles of beer.

04:38:13.170 --> 04:38:14.110
So I lost the first ruble,

04:38:14.120 --> 04:38:15.710
and I won the second 8.

04:38:16.210 --> 04:38:18.130
The total limit income is

04:38:18.140 --> 04:38:19.010
only 7.

04:38:19.970 --> 04:38:22.350
The price is above the limit income.

04:38:25.740 --> 04:38:29.160
And it can be strictly proved, I do not

04:38:29.170 --> 04:38:30.180
use higher mathematics, but simply

04:38:30.200 --> 04:38:30.940
standing on my fingers to explain,

04:38:30.950 --> 04:38:34.640
it can be strictly proved that if the demand

04:38:34.940 --> 04:38:38.920
function is nine, the function of the

04:38:39.020 --> 04:38:40.980
monopolist's limit income is also

04:38:40.990 --> 04:38:43.540
linear, and its inclination is twice

04:38:43.550 --> 04:38:46.180
the inclination of the demand

04:38:47.960 --> 04:38:50.570
function, the prileasing function

04:38:50.580 --> 04:38:51.630
of demand.

04:38:52.470 --> 04:38:55.690
The margin income function is also linear,

04:38:55.700 --> 04:38:58.330
written on a slide, and its slope

04:38:58.340 --> 04:39:02.190
is twice the slope of the demand curve.

04:39:02.810 --> 04:39:03.590
Here, we see that.

04:39:03.830 --> 04:39:05.290
See the demand function.

04:39:05.330 --> 04:39:07.910
Do you see the limit income function?

04:39:07.920 --> 04:39:09.850
The function of the limit income is twice

04:39:09.860 --> 04:39:12.450
as fast as the function of demand.

04:39:12.990 --> 04:39:15.810
Its inclination is twice as much.

04:39:17.940 --> 04:39:19.260
Well, and now let’s see with

04:39:22.170 --> 04:39:24.600
you how you can show on the

04:39:24.610 --> 04:39:28.300
chart of achieving monopoly balance.

04:39:30.240 --> 04:39:31.360
Here what do we see?

04:39:32.100 --> 04:39:34.160
linear function of demand.

04:39:36.500 --> 04:39:39.560
On the other hand, we see the function

04:39:39.570 --> 04:39:40.480
of the limit income.

04:39:41.770 --> 04:39:43.730
The function of the limit income has, as

04:39:43.750 --> 04:39:45.450
I have said, a twice greater inclination

04:39:45.460 --> 04:39:47.790
than the function of the demand for

04:39:47.800 --> 04:39:49.490
the monopoly product.

04:39:49.770 --> 04:39:53.250
And I also put on this picture the functions,

04:39:53.260 --> 04:39:55.870
the classic functions of the marginal

04:39:55.880 --> 04:39:59.190
and average income of the monopolist.

04:39:59.290 --> 04:40:01.530
Excusions, the marginal costs

04:40:01.540 --> 04:40:04.070
of the monopoly and its average

04:40:04.080 --> 04:40:05.110
total costs.

04:40:05.490 --> 04:40:07.670
The function of the marginal,

04:40:07.680 --> 04:40:09.810
I repeat, and the average total cost

04:40:09.820 --> 04:40:11.050
of the monopoly.

04:40:14.710 --> 04:40:17.270
The rules, I said, are always one.

04:40:18.590 --> 04:40:21.090
Profit is maximum at such volume

04:40:21.100 --> 04:40:24.970
of production, where the limit

04:40:26.940 --> 04:40:31.520
income is equal to the limit costs.

04:40:32.740 --> 04:40:37.060
Look at the schedule where we

04:40:37.070 --> 04:40:39.460
cross the functions of the limit

04:40:39.470 --> 04:40:40.740
income and the limit cost.

04:40:41.080 --> 04:40:42.260
You see the crossroads?

04:40:44.680 --> 04:40:49.360
This point determines the QM issue,

04:40:50.640 --> 04:40:54.300
in which the profit of the monopoly is maximum.

04:40:57.940 --> 04:41:00.960
What price will the monopoly pay?

04:41:02.730 --> 04:41:08.090
This price should be looked for on the function on

04:41:08.100 --> 04:41:10.190
the demand curve.

04:41:10.250 --> 04:41:12.750
See, we restore the perpendicular

04:41:12.850 --> 04:41:17.970
from the QM point up to the intersection

04:41:17.980 --> 04:41:21.010
with the demand function.

04:41:21.230 --> 04:41:24.110
And from there we lower the perpendicular to the

04:41:24.120 --> 04:41:25.590
Y axis, to the price axis.

04:41:27.250 --> 04:41:32.830
So, in order to sell QM goods,

04:41:33.330 --> 04:41:35.750
the monopoly must set the PM price

04:41:35.760 --> 04:41:37.850
for its products.

04:41:40.490 --> 04:41:44.210
At this price and such volume of

04:41:44.220 --> 04:41:46.630
production and sales, the profit

04:41:46.640 --> 04:41:49.910
of the monopolist becomes maximum.

04:41:52.550 --> 04:41:53.970
And now finally, please,

04:41:54.790 --> 04:41:59.110
can you show the profit, the

04:41:59.120 --> 04:42:01.150
amount of monopoly profit

04:42:01.160 --> 04:42:02.690
on the chart?

04:42:04.960 --> 04:42:06.520
Well look at.

04:42:06.800 --> 04:42:08.640
What is profit, remember.

04:42:08.800 --> 04:42:09.520
It is easy.

04:42:10.260 --> 04:42:12.580
Profit is the difference between

04:42:12.590 --> 04:42:15.340
revenue and total costs.

04:42:18.460 --> 04:42:20.340
What is profit and revenue?

04:42:24.020 --> 04:42:29.180
This is the price multiplied by the volume of sales.

04:42:30.880 --> 04:42:34.260
So PM multiplied by QM.

04:42:34.520 --> 04:42:36.320
Graphically, this is the area

04:42:36.330 --> 04:42:43.780
of the rectangle O PM EQM.

04:42:47.340 --> 04:42:49.780
Where are the total costs?

04:42:51.720 --> 04:42:53.120
The total cost can be calculated

04:42:53.130 --> 04:42:56.360
by multiplying the average total

04:42:56.370 --> 04:42:59.280
cost again by the volume of

04:42:59.290 --> 04:43:00.520
production.

04:43:01.140 --> 04:43:04.680
If so, then the average total

04:43:04.690 --> 04:43:08.140
cost is equal to the area of the

04:43:08.150 --> 04:43:15.960
rectangle O C FQM.

04:43:17.710 --> 04:43:19.130
That is, it is the area of the

04:43:21.540 --> 04:43:23.810
lower rectangle, and how do we get the profit?

04:43:23.950 --> 04:43:24.930
From the area of the

04:43:24.940 --> 04:43:26.170
upper rectangle, we deduct the area

04:43:26.180 --> 04:43:27.510
of the lower rectangle.

04:43:27.750 --> 04:43:28.610
Accordingly, the profit of the

04:43:28.620 --> 04:43:30.630
monopoly is equal to the area

04:43:30.640 --> 04:43:35.690
of the rectangle C PM E F.

04:43:42.240 --> 04:43:44.760
And a very important conclusion that

04:43:44.770 --> 04:43:46.300
follows from all this.

04:43:46.980 --> 04:43:49.240
Let us remember the perfect competition.

04:43:54.900 --> 04:43:58.980
In perfect competition, the price

04:43:58.990 --> 04:44:01.280
at which the company sells its

04:44:03.250 --> 04:44:06.140
products becomes equal to

04:44:06.150 --> 04:44:09.340
its limit costs at the

04:44:09.350 --> 04:44:11.460
point of balance.

04:44:11.520 --> 04:44:16.020
There is the equation P equal to MC.

04:44:18.070 --> 04:44:20.530
And in the conditions of monopoly domination,

04:44:21.930 --> 04:44:24.310
the monopoly sets a price, look

04:44:26.440 --> 04:44:28.770
at the figure, above the

04:44:28.780 --> 04:44:30.030
limit costs.

04:44:31.190 --> 04:44:32.670
See you?

04:44:33.030 --> 04:44:36.610
The demand line is above the limit

04:44:36.620 --> 04:44:37.650
cost curve.

04:44:40.300 --> 04:44:43.460
The monopoly’s limit costs at the QM issue

04:44:43.470 --> 04:44:46.320
are equal to the OC segment.

04:44:47.640 --> 04:44:50.060
The price of the monopolist, the price that the

04:44:50.070 --> 04:44:52.140
monopolist has set, is equal to the

04:44:52.150 --> 04:44:53.440
OPM segment.

04:44:55.080 --> 04:44:56.780
So, I repeat, the monopoly

04:44:56.960 --> 04:44:58.360
sets a price that exceeds

04:44:58.380 --> 04:45:00.400
the limit costs.

04:45:01.820 --> 04:45:05.200
And hence the most important conclusion is that

04:45:05.210 --> 04:45:13.040
monopolies are able to overpriced the price and underestimate

04:45:13.050 --> 04:45:15.000
the volume of production.

04:45:15.560 --> 04:45:18.280
In the conditions of monopoly power, the

04:45:18.540 --> 04:45:23.220
price is higher and the output is lower

04:45:23.230 --> 04:45:26.600
than in the conditions of competition.

04:45:27.980 --> 04:45:32.960
This is the main claim of society

04:45:32.970 --> 04:45:34.160
to monopoly.

04:45:36.020 --> 04:45:41.060
Monopolies overpriced the price and underestimated

04:45:41.070 --> 04:45:42.820
the volume of production compared to the

04:45:42.830 --> 04:45:44.660
volume of production that would have been

04:45:44.670 --> 04:45:46.580
made if it had had had instead of the

04:45:46.590 --> 04:45:47.660
monopoly competition.

04:45:49.750 --> 04:45:52.490
This is the main basis

04:45:52.500 --> 04:45:55.790
for antimonopoly

04:45:55.800 --> 04:45:57.870
policy.

04:46:01.270 --> 04:46:04.290
Antimonopoly policy is a policy

04:46:04.300 --> 04:46:07.170
of promoting competition.

04:46:09.550 --> 04:46:13.050
In the West, anti-monopoly policy has

04:46:13.060 --> 04:46:18.590
more than a century of experience.

04:46:19.290 --> 04:46:21.530
The first anti-monopoly law in the

04:46:21.540 --> 04:46:23.510
United States, if I am not mistaken,

04:46:23.520 --> 04:46:25.970
was passed in the 1990s of the

04:46:25.980 --> 04:46:28.390
19th century.

04:46:28.670 --> 04:46:32.410
We are in Russia 100 years later.

04:46:33.370 --> 04:46:35.970
Details about the anti-monopoly

04:46:35.980 --> 04:46:40.210
policy are stated in the text of

04:46:40.220 --> 04:46:42.410
this lecture, attached to this

04:46:42.420 --> 04:46:44.150
visual course.

04:46:44.690 --> 04:46:49.310
I will say two words literally that

04:46:49.320 --> 04:46:52.170
antimonopoly policy is a policy

04:46:52.180 --> 04:46:55.270
of promoting competition.

04:46:56.670 --> 04:46:58.390
It is for this it is directed.

04:47:01.780 --> 04:47:05.500
In Russia, a new anti-monopoly

04:47:05.510 --> 04:47:07.680
law has been adopted.

04:47:07.900 --> 04:47:11.320
In 2006, the Competition Protection

04:47:11.330 --> 04:47:12.760
Act was adopted.

04:47:13.360 --> 04:47:16.080
A very useful law contains

04:47:16.090 --> 04:47:18.020
many interesting provisions,

04:47:18.030 --> 04:47:20.500
new provisions that aim to

04:47:20.510 --> 04:47:22.200
prevent monopoly

04:47:22.210 --> 04:47:24.320
domination in the markets.

04:47:28.090 --> 04:47:31.690
But on the other hand, our policy in

04:47:31.700 --> 04:47:33.910
Russia, the policy of the Russian

04:47:33.920 --> 04:47:36.050
government, in this sense, is

04:47:36.060 --> 04:47:37.570
at least ambiguous.

04:47:38.490 --> 04:47:41.670
On the one hand, a very useful anti-

04:47:41.680 --> 04:47:43.910
monopoly law is being adopted.

04:47:45.130 --> 04:47:50.770
More and more large companies

04:47:50.780 --> 04:47:53.650
are being created under

04:47:53.660 --> 04:47:55.410
state control.

04:47:57.060 --> 04:48:00.020
The so-called national champions.

04:48:03.340 --> 04:48:06.380
On the one hand, we are fighting against monopoly.

04:48:06.540 --> 04:48:10.540
On the other hand, we are developing monopoly.

04:48:12.120 --> 04:48:15.240
Rosoboronexport is pulling in its

04:48:15.250 --> 04:48:16.200
entire orbit.

04:48:16.210 --> 04:48:18.300
All new and new enterprises

04:48:18.310 --> 04:48:23.360
form holdings under their control.

04:48:23.660 --> 04:48:26.760
The same is happening in aviation.

04:48:28.470 --> 04:48:30.230
I repeat, you will read more about this

04:48:30.240 --> 04:48:32.810
in the text of the lecture.

04:48:36.130 --> 04:48:39.250
I would only like to be careful

04:48:39.260 --> 04:48:42.650
to question the effectiveness of

04:48:42.660 --> 04:48:43.910
such a policy.

04:48:48.530 --> 04:48:52.430
Most foreign experts and domestic

04:48:52.440 --> 04:48:55.230
experts believe that the policy

04:48:55.530 --> 04:48:58.770
of state support for large

04:48:58.780 --> 04:49:03.930
companies will only lead

04:49:03.940 --> 04:49:06.450
to the fact that these companies

04:49:06.460 --> 04:49:09.510
will become ineffective.

04:49:10.090 --> 04:49:11.870
State support, lack of

04:49:11.990 --> 04:49:14.490
competition will kill business.

04:49:17.430 --> 04:49:19.490
Read more about this in the text

04:49:19.500 --> 04:49:20.910
of the lecture.